1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:17,117
We're here with two up-and-coming stars,

2
00:00:17,183 --> 00:00:18,952
Shin Ye-eun and Lee Jun-young.

3
00:00:19,019 --> 00:00:20,420
Jun-young starred in

4
00:00:20,487 --> 00:00:21,755
D.P.,

5
00:00:21,821 --> 00:00:22,822
Mask Girl,

6
00:00:22,889 --> 00:00:24,124
Weak Hero 2,

7
00:00:24,190 --> 00:00:25,992
<i>and</i> When Life Gives You Tangerines,

8
00:00:26,059 --> 00:00:28,228
-all these amazing projects.
-They're all amazing.

9
00:00:28,294 --> 00:00:30,930
I rarely watch dramas until the end,
but I finished this one.

10
00:00:30,997 --> 00:00:33,199
-<i>When Life Gives You Tangerines</i>?
-I watched it twice.

11
00:00:33,266 --> 00:00:35,635
I still remember the <i>sungnyung</i>,
boiled scorched rice, incident.

12
00:00:35,702 --> 00:00:37,303
When he met the parents.

13
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:41,141
You got up… No.
Did you first say, "I'll do it"?

14
00:00:41,207 --> 00:00:43,410
I thought he wouldn't… Did he get up?

15
00:00:43,476 --> 00:00:45,245
Did IU get up after you?

16
00:00:45,311 --> 00:00:47,113
Was it her mother after that?

17
00:00:47,180 --> 00:00:48,648
You said you watched it twice.

18
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:49,949
My memory is failing me lately.

19
00:00:50,016 --> 00:00:51,651
A FAN WHO HAS A BAD MEMORY

20
00:00:51,718 --> 00:00:54,654
Chef Eun-yeong also said
she was really mad at him

21
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:57,323
while watching
<i>When Life Gives You Tangerines.</i>

22
00:00:57,390 --> 00:00:58,892
He was supposed to get the <i>sungnyung</i>,

23
00:00:58,958 --> 00:01:01,694
but he was just sitting around.
So while I watched, I said,

24
00:01:01,761 --> 00:01:03,830
"Why is that guy still sitting?"

25
00:01:04,130 --> 00:01:05,698
THE NEWLYWED GOT TOO INVESTED

26
00:01:05,765 --> 00:01:07,200
-"Why is he sitting?"
-On the left.

27
00:01:07,267 --> 00:01:08,334
He was sitting on the left.

28
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:11,704
-He only pretended to move, like this.
-That's right.

29
00:01:11,771 --> 00:01:13,740
-Don't people mention that scene often?
-They do.

30
00:01:13,807 --> 00:01:16,209
I once went to a market for a shoot,

31
00:01:16,276 --> 00:01:19,879
And a few ladies came up to me
as if I did something wrong and said,

32
00:01:19,946 --> 00:01:22,082
-"Why did you do that?"
-They would.

33
00:01:22,148 --> 00:01:23,349
I said, "I'm sorry."

34
00:01:23,416 --> 00:01:24,250
AS IF HE'S YEONG-BUM

35
00:01:24,317 --> 00:01:26,086
I remember I kept apologizing.

36
00:01:26,152 --> 00:01:29,322
Your upcoming new drama

37
00:01:29,389 --> 00:01:31,157
also sounds extraordinary.

38
00:01:31,224 --> 00:01:34,027
You're co-starring with Son Hyun-joo,
a veteran actor,

39
00:01:34,094 --> 00:01:38,698
<i>and you'll be portraying a character</i>
<i>who has swapped bodies with him.</i>

40
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:41,468
How did you prepare for this?

41
00:01:41,534 --> 00:01:43,570
Like a preachy boomer?

42
00:01:43,636 --> 00:01:45,505
We met often

43
00:01:45,572 --> 00:01:46,906
and even had a drink of soju

44
00:01:46,973 --> 00:01:49,109
as I tried to copy his habits.

45
00:01:49,175 --> 00:01:51,811
There was one moment that made him
seem very much like a chairman.

46
00:01:51,878 --> 00:01:53,246
He was looking at his phone

47
00:01:53,313 --> 00:01:55,081
with his legs crossed

48
00:01:55,148 --> 00:01:58,184
and one hand on the desk like this.

49
00:01:58,485 --> 00:02:00,153
PRETTY CONVINCING

50
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:02,489
That moment,
he seemed like a real chairman,

51
00:02:02,555 --> 00:02:05,725
so I wanted to bring that habit
into the character.

52
00:02:05,792 --> 00:02:07,627
You'll see many scenes of me doing this.

53
00:02:07,694 --> 00:02:09,963
Yes, you're right.

54
00:02:10,029 --> 00:02:14,100
Also, I had to talk like Hyun-joo.

55
00:02:14,167 --> 00:02:15,869
"You have to eat this." Like that.

56
00:02:15,935 --> 00:02:17,470
Hey, you sound like him.

57
00:02:17,537 --> 00:02:19,672
-Can you do that again?
-He's impersonating Hyun-joo.

58
00:02:19,739 --> 00:02:21,341
You have to eat this.

59
00:02:21,407 --> 00:02:23,710
You have to eat well to work properly.

60
00:02:23,776 --> 00:02:26,779
Something like that.
We'd joke around like that often.

61
00:02:27,046 --> 00:02:28,014
HE SHOWS OFF HIS TRICKS

62
00:02:28,081 --> 00:02:29,716
He has prepared a lot of things.

63
00:02:29,782 --> 00:02:32,652
He's a lottery ticket yet to be scratched.
He has stuff up his sleeve.

64
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:33,887
Here's another story.

65
00:02:33,953 --> 00:02:35,655
While shooting <i>Reborn Rookie,</i>

66
00:02:35,722 --> 00:02:38,024
Jung-hwan was your teacher?

67
00:02:38,091 --> 00:02:41,461
The character I played, Hwang Jun-hyeon,

68
00:02:41,528 --> 00:02:42,595
was a soccer player.

69
00:02:42,662 --> 00:02:44,164
I see.

70
00:02:44,230 --> 00:02:47,734
So there were a few scenes
where I had to kick the soccer ball.

71
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:51,204
I found a video of his lesson
on finding the right timing

72
00:02:51,271 --> 00:02:52,438
<i>-to shoot.</i>
<i>-On my YouTube channel?</i>

73
00:02:52,505 --> 00:02:53,606
You have to move with the ball.

74
00:02:53,673 --> 00:02:55,842
You should've called.
I would've given you a lesson.

75
00:02:56,142 --> 00:02:57,644
THAT'S AWESOME

76
00:02:57,710 --> 00:03:00,046
-I'll contact you next time.
-He's a good teacher.

77
00:03:00,113 --> 00:03:02,215
-You're done shooting, right?
-Yes.

78
00:03:02,549 --> 00:03:03,783
WHAT A SHAME

79
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:06,786
-I could've turned him into a striker.
-Of course.

80
00:03:07,086 --> 00:03:08,655
IT'S SUCH A SHAME

81
00:03:08,721 --> 00:03:10,156
What a shame.

82
00:03:10,223 --> 00:03:12,192
AW, IT'S TOO LATE

83
00:03:12,492 --> 00:03:14,994
IF HE LOOKS RELIEVED, YOU AREN'T MISTAKEN

84
00:03:15,061 --> 00:03:17,397
What if you became a chef?

85
00:03:17,463 --> 00:03:20,099
-What if you swapped bodies with a chef?
-Oh, me?

86
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:22,635
LET'S SEE

87
00:03:22,702 --> 00:03:24,537
-Chef Nam-no.
-What?

88
00:03:24,604 --> 00:03:26,306
-Nam-no?
-For what reason?

89
00:03:26,372 --> 00:03:27,340
You'll regret it.

90
00:03:27,407 --> 00:03:29,776
-What?
-Please swap with me.

91
00:03:29,842 --> 00:03:31,578
You'll swap with him? What?

92
00:03:31,644 --> 00:03:33,846
Let me live just three days as him.

93
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:35,448
BODY-SWAPPING WITH NAM-NO

94
00:03:35,515 --> 00:03:37,417
He has to sit like this.
Nam-no is always like this.

95
00:03:37,483 --> 00:03:38,651
Do you seriously

96
00:03:38,718 --> 00:03:40,787
want to be in that body?

97
00:03:41,087 --> 00:03:42,922
SERIOUSLY…

98
00:03:42,989 --> 00:03:46,593
I've watched so many clips of him eating,

99
00:03:46,659 --> 00:03:49,329
-and he makes everything look so good.
-Yes, he eats deliciously.

100
00:03:49,395 --> 00:03:51,564
Chefs are professionals who make food,

101
00:03:51,631 --> 00:03:52,732
not those who eat.

102
00:03:52,799 --> 00:03:55,335
-That's true.
-All he mentioned was him eating.

103
00:03:55,401 --> 00:03:57,403
Jong-won can't take it anymore.

104
00:03:57,470 --> 00:03:59,205
He's disappointed.

105
00:03:59,272 --> 00:04:01,574
After all, he's sitting right there.

106
00:04:01,641 --> 00:04:03,876
I wanted to cook and eat my own food.

107
00:04:03,943 --> 00:04:05,612
-Cook, then eat.
-You want to eat it too.

108
00:04:05,878 --> 00:04:09,449
REMEMBER… CHEFS ARE THOSE WHO "MAKE" FOOD

109
00:04:09,515 --> 00:04:12,352
Hyun-suk, what if you were to swap bodies

110
00:04:12,418 --> 00:04:14,454
with one of the younger chefs?

111
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:17,657
I also want to live
without back and knee pain.

112
00:04:17,924 --> 00:04:20,893
FUNNY AT FIRST,
AND THEN SOLEMN…

113
00:04:20,960 --> 00:04:22,495
-Whose body is the youngest?
-Who?

114
00:04:22,562 --> 00:04:24,130
But from here, those young bodies look

115
00:04:24,197 --> 00:04:25,131
too challenging.

116
00:04:25,431 --> 00:04:27,967
CHALLENGING

117
00:04:29,202 --> 00:04:32,705
-I'm healthy. And well.
-My back and knee pain may disappear,

118
00:04:32,772 --> 00:04:36,442
-but I don't think I'll be happy there.
-You'd rather be in pain?

119
00:04:36,509 --> 00:04:38,878
-Sung-jun said something like this.
-What is it?

120
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:40,613
"I don't know about others,

121
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,815
but if I were to swap bodies
with Chef Ho-young,

122
00:04:42,882 --> 00:04:44,050
I would be devastated."

123
00:04:44,117 --> 00:04:45,818
-Who said that?
-He did.

124
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:48,755
CLUTCH

125
00:04:48,821 --> 00:04:51,958
He said he'd be devastated
if he swapped bodies with Ho-young.

126
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:54,460
WHAT DID HO-YOUNG EVER DO TO HIM?

127
00:04:54,527 --> 00:04:57,163
I love myself, so I don't want
to swap bodies with anyone.

128
00:04:57,230 --> 00:04:59,232
I just said,
"But definitely not that man."

129
00:04:59,299 --> 00:05:00,466
Hand me a knife.

130
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:02,535
SUNG-JUN IS GOING DOWN TODAY

131
00:05:02,602 --> 00:05:05,138
-There's a reason.
-Let's hear out the reason first. Why?

132
00:05:05,204 --> 00:05:07,307
I wanted to go over
some false accusations.

133
00:05:07,373 --> 00:05:10,076
These days,
I often hear that I have short limbs.

134
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:11,277
-No need to feel bad.
-Accusations?

135
00:05:11,344 --> 00:05:14,247
So if I were to swap bodies,
I want someone with longer limbs.

136
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:15,214
Of course.

137
00:05:15,281 --> 00:05:18,718
But Ho-young also has short limbs,
so it'd be a shame if nothing changed

138
00:05:18,785 --> 00:05:20,953
-even after the swapping.
-That's true.

139
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:24,724
I didn't think that required
such a logical answer.

140
00:05:24,791 --> 00:05:25,925
Well, he gave his take.

141
00:05:25,992 --> 00:05:27,794
This sounds like trouble.

142
00:05:29,429 --> 00:05:32,365
We also asked Ho-young
who he wanted to swap bodies with,

143
00:05:32,432 --> 00:05:34,500
-and he said Sung-jun.
-Why would you do that?

144
00:05:34,801 --> 00:05:36,803
THINGS HAVE GOTTEN QUITE AWKWARD

145
00:05:36,869 --> 00:05:39,172
You're so mean!

146
00:05:39,238 --> 00:05:41,274
-But why?
-Why him?

147
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:43,476
I don't need anything else

148
00:05:43,543 --> 00:05:44,644
but youth.

149
00:05:44,711 --> 00:05:46,112
Oh, because he's young?

150
00:05:46,179 --> 00:05:47,213
I doubt that's enough.

151
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:48,648
As for the short limbs,

152
00:05:48,715 --> 00:05:50,683
mine are the same, so I can adapt faster.

153
00:05:50,983 --> 00:05:52,819
HE'S A GENIUS

154
00:05:52,885 --> 00:05:56,155
-A sudden change can feel weird.
-It may be uncomfortable.

155
00:05:56,222 --> 00:05:58,524
-So that's fine. I just need youth.
-Shorter may be better.

156
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:04,230
There's one more thing
Jun-young is famous for

157
00:06:04,297 --> 00:06:06,399
and that is, he's extremely introverted.

158
00:06:06,466 --> 00:06:07,500
THE INTROVERT NODS

159
00:06:07,567 --> 00:06:09,001
Here's an example.

160
00:06:09,068 --> 00:06:11,571
"He became too shy
and ended the livestream then and there."

161
00:06:11,637 --> 00:06:12,538
What does this mean?

162
00:06:12,605 --> 00:06:15,007
I was streaming live
on my social media account,

163
00:06:15,074 --> 00:06:17,777
and I always had
a certain number of viewers who'd join.

164
00:06:17,844 --> 00:06:21,247
But way more people than that
had joined that day,

165
00:06:21,314 --> 00:06:22,348
and I didn't want to have

166
00:06:22,415 --> 00:06:24,684
a slip of the tongue
so I turned it off then and there.

167
00:06:24,951 --> 00:06:26,719
THE LIVESTREAM BEGINS

168
00:06:26,786 --> 00:06:28,354
SURPRISED

169
00:06:28,654 --> 00:06:30,590
WHY ARE THERE SO MANY PEOPLE?

170
00:06:30,656 --> 00:06:31,657
Six thousand…

171
00:06:32,458 --> 00:06:33,960
CAN'T BELIEVE IT

172
00:06:34,026 --> 00:06:35,061
What…

173
00:06:35,595 --> 00:06:37,630
SUDDENLY ENDS THE STREAM

174
00:06:37,897 --> 00:06:40,466
There are usually around 3,000 people,
but on that day,

175
00:06:40,533 --> 00:06:43,302
-there were about 6,800 people.
-Almost double.

176
00:06:43,369 --> 00:06:45,371
I thought something bad had happened.

177
00:06:45,438 --> 00:06:47,206
That many people usually don't tune in.

178
00:06:47,273 --> 00:06:49,909
I've become more used to it now,

179
00:06:49,976 --> 00:06:51,644
so I rarely look up at the number.

180
00:06:52,645 --> 00:06:54,580
You're more comfortable not seeing it.

181
00:06:54,647 --> 00:06:56,682
That's the method that I learned.

182
00:06:56,749 --> 00:06:59,285
Then it must've been tough for you
when you were active as U-KISS.

183
00:06:59,352 --> 00:07:01,220
-It was really tough.
-I see.

184
00:07:01,287 --> 00:07:02,522
Back then, I was the youngest.

185
00:07:02,588 --> 00:07:04,424
-And performing on stage was fine.
-It was?

186
00:07:04,490 --> 00:07:07,727
-But people are watching.
-I could just get immersed in performing.

187
00:07:07,794 --> 00:07:10,229
I often performed
while looking at the emergency exit.

188
00:07:10,530 --> 00:07:12,031
THE EMERGENCY EXIT?

189
00:07:12,098 --> 00:07:15,968
-It's clearly visible when on stage.
-The green one?

190
00:07:16,035 --> 00:07:19,539
-Does the exit give you peace of mind?
-It was just something to focus on…

191
00:07:19,605 --> 00:07:20,940
Or were you looking for the exit?

192
00:07:21,007 --> 00:07:21,974
SECURING HIS ESCAPE PATH

193
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:24,043
-So he can flee if something happens.
-He can leave.

194
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,878
-It's an emergency exit.
-You probably had

195
00:07:25,945 --> 00:07:27,980
to brace yourself
before starting this shoot.

196
00:07:28,047 --> 00:07:29,849
Do you know where the emergency exit is?

197
00:07:29,916 --> 00:07:31,818
I couldn't find any.

198
00:07:31,884 --> 00:07:33,085
He actually looked for one.

199
00:07:33,152 --> 00:07:35,621
NOT EVEN ONE EXIT
IN THIS ENTIRE 360-DEGREE SET

200
00:07:35,688 --> 00:07:38,458
There is someone among our chefs

201
00:07:38,524 --> 00:07:41,794
who is also evidently
as big an introvert as Jun-young.

202
00:07:41,861 --> 00:07:45,731
This chef has a tip
on overcoming his extreme introversion

203
00:07:45,798 --> 00:07:48,167
and wants to share it.

204
00:07:48,234 --> 00:07:50,970
-It's Chef Jong-won.
-Right.

205
00:07:51,037 --> 00:07:53,372
-He had a rough time here too.
-He did.

206
00:07:53,439 --> 00:07:54,807
I've had

207
00:07:54,874 --> 00:07:57,543
about two turning points in my life.

208
00:07:57,610 --> 00:08:01,247
The first time was when I began to cook
despite my family's opposition.

209
00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:02,882
He actually majored in something else.

210
00:08:02,949 --> 00:08:05,618
The first was when I quit
studying engineering and began to cook.

211
00:08:05,685 --> 00:08:07,453
The second time was when I did

212
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:09,589
the five-minute interim check
with Jung-hwan.

213
00:08:09,989 --> 00:08:12,225
OH, THAT TIME?

214
00:08:12,592 --> 00:08:14,994
JONG-WON'S FIRST EVER
5-MINUTE INTERIM CHECK

215
00:08:15,061 --> 00:08:16,529
The sauce tastes like

216
00:08:16,596 --> 00:08:17,830
a Choi-mpion!

217
00:08:17,897 --> 00:08:20,967
THE INFP PUSHED HIMSELF TOO HARD

218
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:23,603
THOUGH HE WAS TEASED BY JUNG-HWAN FOREVER…

219
00:08:23,870 --> 00:08:25,371
A MEMORABLE SCENE!

220
00:08:25,438 --> 00:08:27,240
So those were my two big turning points.

221
00:08:27,306 --> 00:08:29,542
That wasn't that big of a deal.

222
00:08:29,609 --> 00:08:32,311
It's not easy.
He had to scrape up his energy.

223
00:08:32,378 --> 00:08:35,047
I was pretty much sick in bed for a week.

224
00:08:35,114 --> 00:08:36,649
-Really?
-We didn't know.

225
00:08:36,716 --> 00:08:38,951
I guess it's tough for some people.

226
00:08:39,018 --> 00:08:41,654
But after that day,
the studio felt more like home.

227
00:08:41,721 --> 00:08:43,256
Jun-young should do the check.

228
00:08:43,322 --> 00:08:46,058
-The five-minute check seems helpful.
-He should try.

229
00:08:46,125 --> 00:08:49,061
THE 5-MINUTE INTERIM CHECK
IS GOOD FOR OVERCOMING INTROVERSION…

230
00:08:49,128 --> 00:08:50,630
But only if he wants to.

231
00:08:50,696 --> 00:08:53,232
-All right.
-We hope it becomes a turning point.

232
00:08:53,299 --> 00:08:56,402
-Jung-hwan became his tutor in many ways.
-You're right.

233
00:08:56,469 --> 00:08:59,739
A soccer tutor
and a five-minute interim check tutor.

234
00:08:59,805 --> 00:09:01,574
Should we prepare a soccer ball too?

235
00:09:02,942 --> 00:09:06,212
-Ye-eun, you're also introverted?
-Yes.

236
00:09:06,279 --> 00:09:07,446
She told us herself.

237
00:09:07,513 --> 00:09:09,749
Yes, I'm an introvert too.

238
00:09:09,815 --> 00:09:11,717
-Come on.
-Stop lying.

239
00:09:11,784 --> 00:09:13,786
-She's acting.
-Stop.

240
00:09:13,853 --> 00:09:15,154
Do you want to do the check too?

241
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:16,789
-I can do that much.
-You can?

242
00:09:16,856 --> 00:09:18,190
HER EYES CHANGE IMMEDIATELY

243
00:09:18,257 --> 00:09:20,826
She seems similar to Eun-yeong.

244
00:09:20,893 --> 00:09:22,295
The Eun-yeong of actors.

245
00:09:22,361 --> 00:09:23,696
HER CRAZINESS SHOWS IN HER EYES

246
00:09:23,763 --> 00:09:26,165
-You've seen Eun-yeong dance, right?
-Yes.

247
00:09:26,732 --> 00:09:29,702
-You're so lovely.
-You too. You're such a good dancer.

248
00:09:29,769 --> 00:09:30,903
Really?

249
00:09:30,970 --> 00:09:32,805
IN THEIR OWN LITTLE WORLD

250
00:09:32,872 --> 00:09:34,640
-These two.
-They respect each other.

251
00:09:34,707 --> 00:09:36,442
It's like <i>Street Woman Fighter.</i>

252
00:09:36,509 --> 00:09:38,077
I'm not sure where I saw it,

253
00:09:38,144 --> 00:09:40,580
but I had looked up my own name,

254
00:09:40,646 --> 00:09:43,950
and one of the comments that came up said,
"She's a lot like Shin Ye-eun."

255
00:09:44,016 --> 00:09:47,119
At first, I didn't know what it was,
but then I saw you.

256
00:09:47,186 --> 00:09:48,087
IT MUST'VE BEEN A CLIP LIKE THIS…

257
00:09:48,154 --> 00:09:51,290
After that day,
I never missed <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

258
00:09:51,824 --> 00:09:52,658
YOU GET IT, RIGHT?

259
00:09:52,725 --> 00:09:53,826
People like us

260
00:09:53,893 --> 00:09:56,362
-do it all with our faces.
-Yes, you're right.

261
00:09:56,429 --> 00:09:59,999
-It's easy to get a solo shot.
-Look at them.

262
00:10:00,066 --> 00:10:02,868
-She knows what variety shows require.
-She does.

263
00:10:02,935 --> 00:10:05,137
Even the extremely shy Jun-young

264
00:10:05,204 --> 00:10:07,940
has something he never shies away from.

265
00:10:08,140 --> 00:10:09,041
WHAT IS IT?

266
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:10,943
-It's ramen.
-Ramen?

267
00:10:11,010 --> 00:10:13,112
-He loves ramen.
-He must love ramen.

268
00:10:13,179 --> 00:10:14,914
-Is that right?
-Yes. That's right.

269
00:10:14,981 --> 00:10:17,216
When I was really hooked, I had a streak

270
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:18,551
for two weeks.

271
00:10:18,618 --> 00:10:20,219
-Every day?
-Yes.

272
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:22,488
Do you make your own ramen at home?

273
00:10:22,555 --> 00:10:23,456
Yes.

274
00:10:23,522 --> 00:10:25,424
-You make it?
-You make it yourself?

275
00:10:25,491 --> 00:10:26,993
-It takes a while.
-It takes forever.

276
00:10:27,059 --> 00:10:29,028
-It does take a long time.
-Right?

277
00:10:29,095 --> 00:10:30,796
I have to make the broth,

278
00:10:30,863 --> 00:10:32,798
-make the sauce,
-And the noodles.

279
00:10:32,865 --> 00:10:35,935
then salt the kelp,

280
00:10:36,002 --> 00:10:37,103
marinate eggs,

281
00:10:37,169 --> 00:10:39,405
and make <i>chashu</i>, braised pork, too.
It takes much work.

282
00:10:39,472 --> 00:10:41,307
So I decided to change my method

283
00:10:41,374 --> 00:10:42,975
and use store-bought noodles.

284
00:10:43,042 --> 00:10:45,011
-You used to make them?
-Yes, I bought a noodle maker.

285
00:10:46,412 --> 00:10:47,947
YOU MADE THE NOODLES FROM SCRATCH?

286
00:10:48,014 --> 00:10:49,715
-You made the noodles?
-But I sold it now.

287
00:10:49,782 --> 00:10:51,250
It was way too hard.

288
00:10:51,317 --> 00:10:52,852
-Noodles are tough.
-I was hooked on

289
00:10:52,918 --> 00:10:56,489
<i>kusai tonkotsu</i> ramen, made with broth
that needs to be boiled continuously.

290
00:10:56,555 --> 00:10:59,592
So I tried it
by boiling the broth for 48 hours.

291
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:01,293
-Forty-eight hours?
-You spent

292
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:03,029
all 48 hours at home just boiling that?

293
00:11:03,095 --> 00:11:05,798
While simmering the broth,
I'd read my script, get a short nap,

294
00:11:05,865 --> 00:11:07,433
and check on the broth again.

295
00:11:07,733 --> 00:11:10,102
HE'S PRETTY MUCH A RAMEN EXPERT

296
00:11:10,169 --> 00:11:12,238
Were you pleased with the ramen?

297
00:11:12,304 --> 00:11:13,372
I was.

298
00:11:13,439 --> 00:11:16,409
But if anybody asked
if I were willing to do that

299
00:11:16,475 --> 00:11:17,743
again in the future,

300
00:11:17,810 --> 00:11:19,645
-I'd say never.
-Of course not.

301
00:11:19,712 --> 00:11:20,913
I eat out now.

302
00:11:20,980 --> 00:11:22,982
-I stand in line with gratitude.
-It's better to eat out.

303
00:11:23,049 --> 00:11:24,817
You have a place in Japan

304
00:11:24,884 --> 00:11:27,119
-that lets you eat for free for life?
-You do?

305
00:11:27,186 --> 00:11:30,589
My group loved that place so much,

306
00:11:30,656 --> 00:11:34,260
so when people asked
what we craved the most at concerts,

307
00:11:34,326 --> 00:11:38,064
we'd always mention
the name of that restaurant.

308
00:11:38,130 --> 00:11:41,534
So they made us these gold cards.

309
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:43,069
Is it transferable?

310
00:11:43,135 --> 00:11:44,336
Transferable?

311
00:11:44,403 --> 00:11:47,807
-Well, if I give it to you, that's it.
-Is it?

312
00:11:47,873 --> 00:11:49,275
-Look.
-He has it.

313
00:11:49,909 --> 00:11:51,010
WHIPS OUT THE GOLD CARD

314
00:11:51,077 --> 00:11:53,913
-It's actually gold in color.
-I'm so jealous.

315
00:11:53,979 --> 00:11:55,281
-Free for life?
-That's a thing?

316
00:11:55,347 --> 00:11:59,585
All I have to do is order
and tell them that I have the gold card.

317
00:11:59,652 --> 00:12:00,853
Can you split that in half?

318
00:12:01,420 --> 00:12:02,588
EXCUSE ME?

319
00:12:02,922 --> 00:12:04,223
I CAN SHOW IT LIKE THIS!

320
00:12:04,290 --> 00:12:06,826
-Yes, show them half of it.
-Like this.

321
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:08,494
A SURPRISINGLY SNEAKY TRICK

322
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:09,628
You're crafty.

323
00:12:09,695 --> 00:12:12,331
-Whose idea is that?
-And show it like this?

324
00:12:12,398 --> 00:12:13,599
Back when we had bus tickets,

325
00:12:13,666 --> 00:12:16,268
we'd cut up and make 10 tickets into 12.

326
00:12:16,335 --> 00:12:18,237
The bus tickets?
He's bringing up the old days again.

327
00:12:18,304 --> 00:12:20,906
Have you ever tied a string to a bus token
and taken it back out?

328
00:12:21,273 --> 00:12:22,441
HE KNOWS THE BUS TOKEN

329
00:12:22,508 --> 00:12:23,776
-What's that?
-Are you serious?

330
00:12:23,843 --> 00:12:25,444
-We aren't that old.
-Come on.

331
00:12:26,378 --> 00:12:27,646
SOMEONE STOP THESE OLD DUDES…

332
00:12:27,713 --> 00:12:28,881
You have to be really quick.

333
00:12:28,948 --> 00:12:32,017
-Do these guys know what a bus token is?
-Yes, you have to move swiftly.

334
00:12:32,084 --> 00:12:34,053
-You don't know, right?
-A coin with a hole.

335
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:34,954
-No.
-I'm sure…

336
00:12:35,020 --> 00:12:37,256
-Like coins from the Joseon era.
-I've seen them in history books.

337
00:12:37,323 --> 00:12:39,258
It's like talking about Sangpyeong Tongbo.

338
00:12:39,325 --> 00:12:41,127
NOW TALKING ABOUT THE JOSEON ERA

339
00:12:41,193 --> 00:12:43,929
-We sidetracked for a bit.
-I'm sorry.

340
00:12:43,996 --> 00:12:45,664
He truly is a ramen enthusiast,

341
00:12:45,731 --> 00:12:47,767
and we're about to look into his fridge.

342
00:12:47,833 --> 00:12:49,401
-Do you use this alone?
-Yes.

343
00:12:49,468 --> 00:12:51,470
-I live alone right now.
-How long has it been?

344
00:12:51,537 --> 00:12:53,139
About four or five years.

345
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:55,941
Any inconveniences since you moved out?

346
00:12:56,008 --> 00:12:59,145
Rather, after I established my own space,

347
00:12:59,211 --> 00:13:00,846
I got to use the fridge alone,

348
00:13:00,913 --> 00:13:04,283
so I've been having fun
filling it up and organizing it.

349
00:13:04,350 --> 00:13:05,818
-And he likes to cook.
-Yes.

350
00:13:05,885 --> 00:13:08,754
-He spends 48 hours on broth.
-On making ramen.

351
00:13:08,821 --> 00:13:10,890
He smells like an expert.

352
00:13:10,956 --> 00:13:15,795
Well, Ye-eun here
did not exactly meet our expectations.

353
00:13:16,629 --> 00:13:18,998
Ye-eun was invited
to be on Culinary Class Wars.

354
00:13:19,064 --> 00:13:21,133
-Let's see the pictures.
-Hey.

355
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,535
The egg on the <i>bibim-guksu…</i>

356
00:13:22,601 --> 00:13:24,303
It looks like you split it in half
with your hands.

357
00:13:24,370 --> 00:13:26,205
-I used a knife.
-And that happened?

358
00:13:26,272 --> 00:13:28,007
Look at that <i>gimbap</i> on the very right.

359
00:13:28,073 --> 00:13:30,009
How are the fillings all popping out?

360
00:13:30,075 --> 00:13:31,277
THE VISUALS WERE A BIT SLOPPY…

361
00:13:31,343 --> 00:13:33,946
-We present Ye-eun's fridge!
-Fridge!

362
00:13:34,013 --> 00:13:35,347
I don't have too much food.

363
00:13:35,848 --> 00:13:39,485
SHE DIDN'T HAVE TOO MANY INGREDIENTS…

364
00:13:40,052 --> 00:13:42,588
Let's look forward
to seeing Jun-young's fridge today.

365
00:13:42,655 --> 00:13:44,390
A man who's serious about ramen,

366
00:13:44,456 --> 00:13:46,692
Jun-young's fridge
is about to be presented.

367
00:13:46,759 --> 00:13:48,828
We present Jun-young's fridge!

368
00:13:50,129 --> 00:13:53,265
HUH? WHAT?

369
00:13:53,532 --> 00:13:55,334
PRESENTING JUN-YOUNG'S FRIDGE

370
00:13:56,335 --> 00:13:57,636
-Hey, what?
-Whoa.

371
00:13:57,703 --> 00:13:58,904
What is this?

372
00:13:58,971 --> 00:14:02,007
Look at how organized he is.
He labeled everything.

373
00:14:02,074 --> 00:14:03,709
Those tubs are for commercial kitchens.

374
00:14:03,776 --> 00:14:06,245
-He's almost like a chef.
-Isn't he?

375
00:14:06,579 --> 00:14:07,680
GASP!

376
00:14:07,746 --> 00:14:09,415
You staged that, didn't you?

377
00:14:09,481 --> 00:14:10,950
No, I'd never do that.

378
00:14:11,016 --> 00:14:12,551
-It does look staged, right?
-Was it?

379
00:14:12,618 --> 00:14:13,919
-Yes.
-A little.

380
00:14:13,986 --> 00:14:14,987
WANTS TO BELIEVE IT WAS STAGED…

381
00:14:15,054 --> 00:14:18,224
-It's giving Chef Jong-won vibes.
-Right?

382
00:14:18,290 --> 00:14:20,693
I'm feeling quite at ease.

383
00:14:20,759 --> 00:14:23,295
-Are you?
-Did you feel uncomfortable last week?

384
00:14:23,662 --> 00:14:25,464
HE'S BEEN FOUND OUT

385
00:14:25,898 --> 00:14:27,533
…HEHE

386
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:30,002
Why did you do all this?
You didn't have to.

387
00:14:30,069 --> 00:14:33,572
At first, I stashed everything in
without organizing them.

388
00:14:33,639 --> 00:14:38,644
But I have an older friend
who runs a Japanese-style pub,

389
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:40,779
so I asked where I could get those

390
00:14:40,846 --> 00:14:41,714
and started to do that.

391
00:14:41,780 --> 00:14:43,749
May I give just one tip?

392
00:14:43,816 --> 00:14:45,150
You used tape to label them, right?

393
00:14:45,217 --> 00:14:48,120
-You should cut it neatly with scissors.
-Right.

394
00:14:48,187 --> 00:14:49,355
-No ripping.
-The edges.

395
00:14:49,421 --> 00:14:50,389
Why?

396
00:14:51,290 --> 00:14:52,591
-It looks bad.
-So it looks better?

397
00:14:52,958 --> 00:14:56,695
IF YOU CAN, DO IT PERFECTLY

398
00:14:56,762 --> 00:14:58,197
He's free to rip it with his hand.

399
00:14:58,264 --> 00:15:00,966
-Cut it neatly with scissors.
-Scissors?

400
00:15:02,134 --> 00:15:03,002
Look at these.

401
00:15:03,068 --> 00:15:04,370
Scallops.

402
00:15:04,436 --> 00:15:07,072
Dried clam meat.
Red pepper powder. Bonito stock.

403
00:15:07,139 --> 00:15:09,308
Shiitake. Whole garlic cloves. Ginger.

404
00:15:09,375 --> 00:15:12,678
-Green onion, whites.
-And greens.

405
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:14,647
You've separated the greens and whites?

406
00:15:14,713 --> 00:15:16,181
The bottom and the top.

407
00:15:16,248 --> 00:15:18,817
I often use the green portion
to make broth,

408
00:15:18,884 --> 00:15:22,354
and the white portion
is for braising and grilling.

409
00:15:22,421 --> 00:15:24,390
-That way, it's delicious.
-You've separated these?

410
00:15:24,456 --> 00:15:26,692
-And noodles.
-The store-bought ones.

411
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:29,028
Can I ask
for the types of ramen you've made?

412
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:30,963
<i>Tonkotsu</i> ramen. And with those

413
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:34,033
scallops and clam meat,
I've whipped up something simpler,

414
00:15:34,099 --> 00:15:36,368
called <i>shio</i> ramen.

415
00:15:36,435 --> 00:15:37,937
How long did that take?

416
00:15:38,003 --> 00:15:39,371
That one wasn't so bad.

417
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:41,273
I can do it in three to four hours.

418
00:15:41,340 --> 00:15:42,675
Three to four hours isn't bad?

419
00:15:43,075 --> 00:15:45,144
THAT'S A MAN WHO'S SERIOUS ABOUT RAMEN

420
00:15:45,210 --> 00:15:46,111
What else?

421
00:15:46,178 --> 00:15:49,648
I've lately been using anchovies
to make <i>niboshi</i> ramen.

422
00:15:49,715 --> 00:15:51,116
-There are anchovies here.
-Yes.

423
00:15:51,183 --> 00:15:54,219
-There's a whole box. For the broth?
-He has a box.

424
00:15:54,286 --> 00:15:56,422
Those were recommended
by someone who owns a ramen place.

425
00:15:56,488 --> 00:15:58,290
How long does that ramen take?

426
00:15:58,357 --> 00:15:59,692
It takes a bit of time.

427
00:15:59,758 --> 00:16:00,659
Eight hours.

428
00:16:00,726 --> 00:16:02,261
-Eight hours.
-Eight hours?

429
00:16:02,328 --> 00:16:04,129
Aren't you busy?

430
00:16:04,196 --> 00:16:07,032
So I only make it
when I have two full days off.

431
00:16:07,099 --> 00:16:09,401
It also gives me a sense of achievement.

432
00:16:10,069 --> 00:16:12,438
You must like eating
something you made yourself.

433
00:16:12,504 --> 00:16:14,873
When I read the script
while the broth simmers,

434
00:16:14,940 --> 00:16:16,775
it makes me feel at ease, so I love it.

435
00:16:16,842 --> 00:16:18,243
That's how he unwinds.

436
00:16:18,310 --> 00:16:21,380
All right, then.
We have a while left in this shoot,

437
00:16:21,447 --> 00:16:24,149
so can you make us something
that'll take four hours?

438
00:16:24,216 --> 00:16:25,784
-The simplified version.
-Simplified.

439
00:16:26,051 --> 00:16:28,187
JUST THINKING OF IT MAKES HIM HAPPY

440
00:16:28,253 --> 00:16:30,990
Do you make the dish like that
and eat it alone?

441
00:16:31,056 --> 00:16:32,591
-Yes.
-And that's it?

442
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:36,195
Well, I can't make
too much broth at a time,

443
00:16:36,261 --> 00:16:38,464
so it's just enough for two portions.

444
00:16:38,530 --> 00:16:41,533
-You spend eight hours on two portions?
-To eat two bowls?

445
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,769
The way he studies his character
and recipes show

446
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:45,404
the dedication he has to his craft.

447
00:16:45,471 --> 00:16:47,406
Do you only make ramen at home?

448
00:16:47,473 --> 00:16:48,607
No, I make other dishes too.

449
00:16:48,674 --> 00:16:50,642
-You cook other things?
-I make pasta and stuff.

450
00:16:50,709 --> 00:16:54,346
I see some basil, celery,
dill, and arugula here.

451
00:16:54,413 --> 00:16:56,348
I use them to make Bolognese sauce.

452
00:16:56,415 --> 00:16:58,517
That's delicious.
But it also takes a while.

453
00:16:58,584 --> 00:17:00,619
-Rosemary, parsley,
-Rosemary?

454
00:17:00,686 --> 00:17:02,254
parsley stems.

455
00:17:02,321 --> 00:17:03,489
Pepetoncino.

456
00:17:03,555 --> 00:17:05,591
-Peppertones?
-What's peppertones?

457
00:17:05,657 --> 00:17:07,726
-Peppers?
-Peppa… What is this?

458
00:17:07,793 --> 00:17:09,094
-Peperoncino!
-Peperoncino?

459
00:17:09,161 --> 00:17:10,696
Guan… Guanciale?

460
00:17:10,763 --> 00:17:12,231
-Guanciale?
-He has guanciale?

461
00:17:12,297 --> 00:17:13,632
-Guanciale?
-How do you have guanciale?

462
00:17:13,699 --> 00:17:14,700
What's guanciale?

463
00:17:14,767 --> 00:17:17,002
It's cured pork.

464
00:17:17,069 --> 00:17:18,804
So you bought guanciale?

465
00:17:18,871 --> 00:17:21,140
-For carbonara.
-Yes, it's for carbonara.

466
00:17:21,206 --> 00:17:22,908
He should compete in <i>Culinary Class Wars.</i>

467
00:17:22,975 --> 00:17:25,310
I think he should be the one to compete.

468
00:17:25,377 --> 00:17:29,148
I don't think I should've come today.
I shouldn't have come with him.

469
00:17:29,214 --> 00:17:33,218
I keep hearing Ye-eun mumbling.
What are you saying?

470
00:17:33,285 --> 00:17:34,720
That I shouldn't have come.

471
00:17:35,854 --> 00:17:36,855
No, we're glad to have you.

472
00:17:36,922 --> 00:17:38,524
It's not like that at all.

473
00:17:38,590 --> 00:17:41,593
Your episode was already aired.

474
00:17:41,660 --> 00:17:42,694
-It went on air.
-It's over.

475
00:17:42,761 --> 00:17:43,595
It is, right?

476
00:17:43,662 --> 00:17:45,931
It would've been worse
if the orders were switched.

477
00:17:45,998 --> 00:17:48,300
Your fridge looks so good.

478
00:17:48,367 --> 00:17:50,469
You have parsley here,

479
00:17:50,536 --> 00:17:53,138
and you've separated the stems.

480
00:17:53,205 --> 00:17:55,207
I didn't want to waste them.

481
00:17:55,274 --> 00:17:57,409
They come in long stalks, right?

482
00:17:57,476 --> 00:18:00,946
So I just throw the stems in
when I cook pasta.

483
00:18:01,013 --> 00:18:03,715
I saw some people who did that.

484
00:18:03,782 --> 00:18:05,918
Those stems are often used

485
00:18:05,984 --> 00:18:07,119
to cook clams

486
00:18:07,186 --> 00:18:10,022
or to eliminate fishy smells.

487
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:13,025
-You can use them to make broth too.
-Yes, that's done often.

488
00:18:13,092 --> 00:18:15,794
Do you have any questions
on how to use a particular ingredient?

489
00:18:15,861 --> 00:18:18,263
-Dill.
-Dill.

490
00:18:18,330 --> 00:18:20,332
I'm still not sure how I should use them.

491
00:18:20,399 --> 00:18:23,802
Chefs, please share some ways
he can use dill.

492
00:18:23,869 --> 00:18:25,370
-They go well with dairy products.
-Yes.

493
00:18:25,437 --> 00:18:28,140
-Mix it with sour cream.
-Right.

494
00:18:28,207 --> 00:18:29,875
If you want to use them for a long time,

495
00:18:29,942 --> 00:18:32,878
you can mix them with butter or oil,

496
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:35,314
freeze them, and use them as needed.

497
00:18:35,380 --> 00:18:36,582
Dill oil.

498
00:18:36,648 --> 00:18:38,984
-Ye-eun, how do you use--
-I know what dill is.

499
00:18:39,384 --> 00:18:40,519
VERY SENSITIVE

500
00:18:40,586 --> 00:18:42,054
I didn't say you didn't know.

501
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:45,324
I was just asking how you use dill.

502
00:18:45,390 --> 00:18:46,458
Do you know what dill is?

503
00:18:46,525 --> 00:18:47,826
You know.

504
00:18:47,893 --> 00:18:49,294
It goes on steaks,

505
00:18:49,361 --> 00:18:53,565
on top of the white sauce.

506
00:18:53,632 --> 00:18:55,200
Isn't that herb called dill?

507
00:18:55,267 --> 00:18:57,603
The garnish on top of steaks.
Is that right?

508
00:18:57,669 --> 00:18:59,538
Dill butter often goes on top.

509
00:18:59,605 --> 00:19:00,839
-Dill butter.
-It'll look white.

510
00:19:00,906 --> 00:19:02,941
So the white thing I saw was butter!

511
00:19:03,008 --> 00:19:06,078
Ye-eun knows what it is. She knows too.

512
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:09,882
We already saw the dishes
Ye-eun had made,

513
00:19:09,948 --> 00:19:12,684
and Jun-young
also sounds like a really good cook.

514
00:19:12,751 --> 00:19:15,354
He sent us some pictures
of the dishes he made.

515
00:19:15,420 --> 00:19:18,157
-I can't wait to see it.
-How well does he cook for himself?

516
00:19:18,223 --> 00:19:19,258
Let's find out.

517
00:19:19,691 --> 00:19:21,193
AMAZED

518
00:19:21,260 --> 00:19:22,361
He's so good.

519
00:19:22,427 --> 00:19:23,529
Let's find out.

520
00:19:23,829 --> 00:19:26,431
LOOKS PROFESSIONAL

521
00:19:26,498 --> 00:19:27,833
Look at that mapo tofu.

522
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:30,169
Truffle. That's truffle pasta.

523
00:19:30,235 --> 00:19:33,472
Why did they show
only four of my pictures and five of his?

524
00:19:33,539 --> 00:19:36,341
I sent like 30 pictures, Writer!

525
00:19:36,408 --> 00:19:38,644
LAUGHING OUT LOUD

526
00:19:39,044 --> 00:19:41,747
FLOP

527
00:19:41,813 --> 00:19:42,948
What's wrong?

528
00:19:43,015 --> 00:19:45,384
I sent 30 pictures,

529
00:19:45,450 --> 00:19:46,818
but they only showed four.

530
00:19:47,753 --> 00:19:49,288
And the ones that look
the easiest to make.

531
00:19:49,588 --> 00:19:51,590
I'VE MADE LOTS OF OTHER GOOD DISHES TOO…

532
00:19:51,657 --> 00:19:53,325
Why did they pick out

533
00:19:53,392 --> 00:19:56,061
only the ones that obviously look
really nice for his episode?

534
00:19:56,128 --> 00:19:57,930
How many have you sent us?

535
00:19:57,996 --> 00:20:00,098
All of those and maybe one or two more.

536
00:20:00,666 --> 00:20:02,701
SCRIPTWRITER…

537
00:20:03,268 --> 00:20:04,469
I can't look her in the eyes.

538
00:20:04,536 --> 00:20:07,206
-Tell us about the five dishes, Jun-young.
-From the left.

539
00:20:07,272 --> 00:20:10,542
The leftmost one
was the <i>niboshi</i> ramen I tried making.

540
00:20:10,609 --> 00:20:12,844
I made that meat topping
with chicken tenderloin.

541
00:20:12,911 --> 00:20:15,013
He makes them very properly.

542
00:20:15,080 --> 00:20:19,451
-The next one is butter chicken curry.
-Butter chicken curry.

543
00:20:19,518 --> 00:20:23,288
I roasted the spices over there

544
00:20:23,355 --> 00:20:25,524
and crushed them in a mortar.

545
00:20:25,591 --> 00:20:28,560
-He even has a mortar at home.
-He has it right here.

546
00:20:28,627 --> 00:20:30,095
And a scale right next to it.

547
00:20:30,162 --> 00:20:31,496
-He's a pro.
-He is.

548
00:20:31,563 --> 00:20:32,764
He's serious about cooking.

549
00:20:32,831 --> 00:20:35,634
-And that's Sichuan style mapo tofu.
-Right.

550
00:20:35,701 --> 00:20:39,071
-You made mapo tofu too?
-Yes, I like it.

551
00:20:39,137 --> 00:20:41,039
What's the white thing next to mapo tofu?

552
00:20:41,106 --> 00:20:43,342
-Pasta.
-That? Pasta.

553
00:20:43,408 --> 00:20:45,310
Is that truffle on the pasta?

554
00:20:45,377 --> 00:20:46,511
You're right.

555
00:20:46,578 --> 00:20:47,980
He's the real deal.

556
00:20:48,046 --> 00:20:50,115
Wasn't that last picture
taken at a restaurant?

557
00:20:50,182 --> 00:20:52,384
-Japanese home cooking.
-It's Japanese home cooking.

558
00:20:52,451 --> 00:20:54,419
When I lived in Japan for a while,

559
00:20:54,486 --> 00:20:55,954
I learned lots of Japanese recipes

560
00:20:56,021 --> 00:20:58,523
from the housekeeper we had.

561
00:20:58,590 --> 00:21:01,693
-Look at Ye-eun.
-She's downing water.

562
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,362
She must feel thirsty.

563
00:21:03,428 --> 00:21:05,397
Do you feel upset?

564
00:21:05,464 --> 00:21:08,300
-No. He's a good cook, and so am I.
-He is. Yes.

565
00:21:08,367 --> 00:21:10,535
Which one of you
should compete in <i>Culinary Class Wars?</i>

566
00:21:11,236 --> 00:21:12,904
We just have different styles.

567
00:21:13,205 --> 00:21:14,306
A GREAT ANSWER

568
00:21:14,373 --> 00:21:15,774
Yes, you have different styles.

569
00:21:15,841 --> 00:21:19,611
-Yes, some people cook like us!
-You should all compete.

570
00:21:19,678 --> 00:21:21,647
HEHE

571
00:21:21,713 --> 00:21:25,651
Do you need to make it look so pretty
if you're eating that by yourself?

572
00:21:25,717 --> 00:21:27,853
It's to send to my parents and show them

573
00:21:27,919 --> 00:21:29,154
that I'm doing well.

574
00:21:29,454 --> 00:21:31,156
FOR HIS PARENTS' PEACE OF MIND

575
00:21:31,223 --> 00:21:32,858
Like, "Don't worry about me."

576
00:21:32,924 --> 00:21:35,327
Look at all these sauces.

577
00:21:35,394 --> 00:21:37,362
He makes Chinese dishes too,
like mapo tofu.

578
00:21:37,429 --> 00:21:39,298
<i>Doubanjiang </i>and more.

579
00:21:39,364 --> 00:21:42,067
-Eun-yeong must have an advantage.
-He has lots.

580
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:44,903
-Wait, isn't this caviar?
-Caviar?

581
00:21:44,970 --> 00:21:47,039
-I found caviar.
-I see.

582
00:21:47,105 --> 00:21:48,774
-Whoa.
-That's caviar?

583
00:21:49,274 --> 00:21:53,245
He's not here, but while watching
Chef Kang-rok's YouTube channel,

584
00:21:53,312 --> 00:21:57,649
I saw him make
something called <i>oeuf</i> mayonnaise

585
00:21:57,716 --> 00:21:59,751
topped with caviar.

586
00:21:59,818 --> 00:22:02,521
-They go well together.
-I got curious and tried it,

587
00:22:02,587 --> 00:22:03,522
and it was very good.

588
00:22:06,024 --> 00:22:07,326
The freezer.

589
00:22:07,392 --> 00:22:10,429
What's this?
Why do you have things in bulk?

590
00:22:10,495 --> 00:22:12,597
-I use it to make <i>chashu.</i>
<i>-Chashu?</i>

591
00:22:12,664 --> 00:22:14,399
You make it at home?

592
00:22:14,466 --> 00:22:15,767
Wait a second.

593
00:22:15,834 --> 00:22:17,235
Hey, Jun-young.

594
00:22:17,302 --> 00:22:18,437
-Yes?
-Why do you have

595
00:22:18,503 --> 00:22:22,507
-two whole chickens if you live alone?
-That's a lot.

596
00:22:22,574 --> 00:22:24,843
-It must be for broth.
-My gosh.

597
00:22:24,910 --> 00:22:27,979
I use them to make ramen broth
or to make chicken stock.

598
00:22:28,046 --> 00:22:28,980
He makes chicken stock?

599
00:22:29,047 --> 00:22:31,650
-Chicken stock?
-He makes chicken stock?

600
00:22:31,950 --> 00:22:33,185
LOVES TO COOK FROM SCRATCH

601
00:22:33,251 --> 00:22:34,653
It's even crazier over here.

602
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:38,090
-It's like a library.
-Like a fine dining restaurant.

603
00:22:38,156 --> 00:22:41,626
He has star anise,
bay leaves, cloves, and…

604
00:22:41,693 --> 00:22:43,929
IT'LL TAKE FOREVER TO READ OUT EVERYTHING

605
00:22:43,995 --> 00:22:45,697
What's "Love"?

606
00:22:45,764 --> 00:22:46,865
-Love?
-Love?

607
00:22:46,932 --> 00:22:48,066
Right.

608
00:22:48,133 --> 00:22:49,368
-MSG.
-Right.

609
00:22:49,434 --> 00:22:51,570
-"Love."
-MSG.

610
00:22:51,636 --> 00:22:52,637
Why did you call it "Love"?

611
00:22:52,704 --> 00:22:54,072
A BIG SMILE

612
00:22:54,139 --> 00:22:55,807
I went to a friend's restaurant,

613
00:22:55,874 --> 00:22:59,511
and his MSG tub read "Love"
in huge letters.

614
00:22:59,578 --> 00:23:02,080
I asked what it was because it was cute,
and he said it was MSG.

615
00:23:02,147 --> 00:23:04,383
-MSG.
-MSG is love.

616
00:23:04,449 --> 00:23:06,051
-That's why.
-So you do use MSG.

617
00:23:06,118 --> 00:23:07,285
-I do.
-He has to.

618
00:23:07,352 --> 00:23:08,687
Yes, he does.

619
00:23:08,754 --> 00:23:10,522
He uses MSG too.

620
00:23:10,589 --> 00:23:11,690
-Of course.
-She looks happy.

621
00:23:11,757 --> 00:23:14,025
You suddenly look very pleased.

622
00:23:14,092 --> 00:23:16,661
-Did you see this? Bonito flakes.
-Bonito flakes.

623
00:23:16,728 --> 00:23:18,764
HUGE

624
00:23:18,830 --> 00:23:21,466
-Those were recommended to me too.
-And the kelp?

625
00:23:21,533 --> 00:23:23,902
Those flakes
are actually used at restaurants.

626
00:23:24,703 --> 00:23:27,939
We looked through an expert cook's fridge!

627
00:23:28,006 --> 00:23:29,875
FINISHED LOOKING THROUGH
THE EXPERT'S FRIDGE

628
00:23:30,909 --> 00:23:32,811
He actually does that at home?

629
00:23:32,878 --> 00:23:35,147
-That's crazy.
-We were so surprised.

630
00:23:35,213 --> 00:23:39,351
I can sense some nervousness
in the chefs' eyes.

631
00:23:39,418 --> 00:23:43,288
And now, let's find out
what Jun-young's orders are.

632
00:23:43,355 --> 00:23:44,890
What does he want to eat?

633
00:23:46,625 --> 00:23:48,460
When Life Hooks You on Ramen.

634
00:23:48,527 --> 00:23:49,795
-Nice title.
-As expected.

635
00:23:49,861 --> 00:23:51,797
Making ramen in 15 minutes is too harsh.

636
00:23:51,863 --> 00:23:55,200
-He spends eight hours making broth.
-Tell us about it.

637
00:23:55,267 --> 00:23:57,669
I do not know much,

638
00:23:57,736 --> 00:24:01,940
but these chefs
must have skills on another level.

639
00:24:02,007 --> 00:24:03,642
So I was wondering

640
00:24:03,708 --> 00:24:05,677
if they could make me ramen

641
00:24:05,744 --> 00:24:10,115
that even I can try to make in 15 minutes.

642
00:24:10,182 --> 00:24:13,118
He used to spend 48 hours,
and 8 hours with a simplified recipe,

643
00:24:13,185 --> 00:24:15,153
-but he must find it tedious now.
-A little.

644
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:17,923
So he wants to do it in 15 minutes.

645
00:24:17,989 --> 00:24:20,125
He wants a 15-minute recipe.

646
00:24:20,192 --> 00:24:22,427
-That's a part of the reason.
-It is, right?

647
00:24:22,494 --> 00:24:24,596
Let's look at the next one.
The second order.

648
00:24:24,663 --> 00:24:26,231
What's his next order?

649
00:24:26,298 --> 00:24:29,000
<i>-Chef & My Fridge</i> Office Body Swap.
-Body Swap.

650
00:24:29,067 --> 00:24:30,035
What's this?

651
00:24:30,101 --> 00:24:31,970
Just like the premise of my drama,

652
00:24:32,037 --> 00:24:35,240
the two contenders will switch

653
00:24:35,307 --> 00:24:38,176
the style of their cooking.

654
00:24:38,243 --> 00:24:39,711
They'll swap cuisines.

655
00:24:40,078 --> 00:24:41,613
OH?

656
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:44,249
-They'll switch. This will be a fun one.
-It sounds fun.

657
00:24:44,316 --> 00:24:46,485
Since it's a body swap,
should they change behavior

658
00:24:46,551 --> 00:24:49,020
-and the way they speak too?
-Actions, words, everything.

659
00:24:49,087 --> 00:24:51,389
-Not just the type of cuisine.
-Everything.

660
00:24:51,456 --> 00:24:52,924
GULPING

661
00:24:52,991 --> 00:24:54,793
The previous episode's orders
were great too.

662
00:24:54,860 --> 00:24:56,328
Why are you suddenly gulping again?

663
00:24:56,394 --> 00:24:58,196
This order sounds more interesting, right?

664
00:24:58,263 --> 00:24:59,397
No.

665
00:25:00,632 --> 00:25:02,868
I thought,
"He's good at promoting his drama."

666
00:25:05,070 --> 00:25:06,204
"He's good at promoting his drama."

667
00:25:06,271 --> 00:25:09,407
-Thank you.
-She must feel regretful right now.

668
00:25:09,474 --> 00:25:12,577
She should've done something like,
"Something Delicious to Eat on the Edge."

669
00:25:12,644 --> 00:25:17,115
Now, four chefs
who didn't cook last week remain.

670
00:25:17,182 --> 00:25:19,184
First come, first served.

671
00:25:19,251 --> 00:25:21,152
Who wants to go?

672
00:25:21,219 --> 00:25:23,288
-Me.
-Yes, of course, Ho-young is in.

673
00:25:23,355 --> 00:25:24,656
I'll make ramen.

674
00:25:24,723 --> 00:25:26,358
-How can anyone beat him?
-That's right.

675
00:25:26,424 --> 00:25:28,760
I can't beat him.
I'm not joining that one.

676
00:25:28,827 --> 00:25:31,696
-Ho-young joins the ramen round.
-The second one is open.

677
00:25:31,763 --> 00:25:34,866
You'll have to change your style
for the second round.

678
00:25:34,933 --> 00:25:36,501
It depends on who you'll fight.

679
00:25:36,568 --> 00:25:41,540
One Chinese chef, one Korean and French,
and one Italian chef.

680
00:25:41,606 --> 00:25:43,775
I'll join the second round.

681
00:25:43,842 --> 00:25:45,577
-The body swap.
-I see.

682
00:25:45,644 --> 00:25:48,380
-You don't know who'll join you.
-Will you channel the other person?

683
00:25:48,446 --> 00:25:49,447
Western cuisine it is.

684
00:25:49,514 --> 00:25:52,017
-She has the advantage, period.
-Are we going to see Amy Park?

685
00:25:52,083 --> 00:25:54,653
I, Amy Park,

686
00:25:54,719 --> 00:25:56,755
have cooked Italian food

687
00:25:56,821 --> 00:25:58,356
as well as Cantonese.

688
00:25:58,423 --> 00:26:01,192
-I have many experiences.
-Yes, of course.

689
00:26:01,259 --> 00:26:04,763
-And I'm always up for new challenges.
-I'm sure.

690
00:26:04,829 --> 00:26:08,300
I thought it'd be nice to cook French
by switching with Chef Jong-won.

691
00:26:08,667 --> 00:26:11,903
I… HAVE TO BE… EUN-YEONG?

692
00:26:11,970 --> 00:26:13,838
That means he'll have to dance.

693
00:26:14,339 --> 00:26:15,774
I HAVE TO… DO THAT?

694
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:17,709
-A bolt out of the blue.
-Jong-won will

695
00:26:17,776 --> 00:26:19,811
-have to dance to "Queencard."
-Yes.

696
00:26:19,878 --> 00:26:22,847
-Yes, he has to swap bodies with me.
-When he tells us about his dish.

697
00:26:22,914 --> 00:26:25,817
-With those crazy dead eyes.
-The dead eyes.

698
00:26:26,051 --> 00:26:27,586
LIKE THIS?

699
00:26:27,652 --> 00:26:28,787
Not bad.

700
00:26:28,853 --> 00:26:30,155
Jong-won, will you join her?

701
00:26:30,221 --> 00:26:31,923
-Are you up for it?
-Are you?

702
00:26:31,990 --> 00:26:36,394
Instead of <i>Emily in Paris,</i>
let's find out what Amy in Paris is like.

703
00:26:36,461 --> 00:26:39,230
-I'll do the body swap.
-He joins the body swap round!

704
00:26:39,297 --> 00:26:41,766
Then it's been decided.

705
00:26:41,833 --> 00:26:43,401
Eun-yeong versus Jong-won.

706
00:26:43,468 --> 00:26:46,104
-Sam automatically has to make ramen.
-Ramen.

707
00:26:46,171 --> 00:26:47,372
Hey, wait.

708
00:26:47,439 --> 00:26:50,375
-I don't think he should do that.
-Can you make ramen?

709
00:26:50,442 --> 00:26:52,444
You've had ramen, right?

710
00:26:52,510 --> 00:26:54,045
-I've had it.
-"Have you had it?"

711
00:26:54,112 --> 00:26:56,181
Are you okay with making ramen?

712
00:26:56,247 --> 00:26:58,350
-I'll do my best.
-All right.

713
00:26:58,416 --> 00:27:00,719
The first round is the ramen cook-off.

714
00:27:00,785 --> 00:27:03,221
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin
between Ho-young and Sam!

715
00:27:05,423 --> 00:27:09,761
<i>This is the first round</i>
<i>played with Jun-young's ingredients.</i>

716
00:27:09,828 --> 00:27:13,832
Two men who once coveted
the show's Best Couple Award.

717
00:27:13,898 --> 00:27:15,800
<i>But after the team match,</i>

718
00:27:15,867 --> 00:27:18,269
they have become
each other's sworn enemies.

719
00:27:18,336 --> 00:27:21,840
It's a round between
Chef Sam Kim and Chef Jung Ho-young.

720
00:27:21,906 --> 00:27:23,608
You're about to make Japanese ramen,

721
00:27:23,675 --> 00:27:26,244
-so Ho-young must have an advantage.
-Yes.

722
00:27:26,311 --> 00:27:28,747
But I guess Sam has a different idea.

723
00:27:28,813 --> 00:27:29,648
Is that so?

724
00:27:29,714 --> 00:27:32,217
-We have a transcript of his statement.
-We do.

725
00:27:32,283 --> 00:27:35,487
"Ho-young will make
a very ordinary ramen."

726
00:27:35,553 --> 00:27:37,922
-Something generic?
-Yes, something generic.

727
00:27:37,989 --> 00:27:40,759
I didn't say it that harshly.

728
00:27:40,825 --> 00:27:42,027
But something like that.

729
00:27:42,093 --> 00:27:43,395
SPILLING THE TRUTH

730
00:27:43,461 --> 00:27:44,863
It's true!

731
00:27:44,929 --> 00:27:46,765
I said he would make

732
00:27:46,831 --> 00:27:50,869
a kind of ramen that
Jun-young had previously eaten before.

733
00:27:50,935 --> 00:27:52,103
It's all the same.

734
00:27:52,170 --> 00:27:54,606
So you think he'll show zero creativity?

735
00:27:54,673 --> 00:27:56,074
Something that everyone makes.

736
00:27:56,141 --> 00:27:57,442
Actually, Sam

737
00:27:57,509 --> 00:27:59,177
doesn't know much about ramen.

738
00:28:00,979 --> 00:28:02,947
"My dear Sam knows nothing about ramen."

739
00:28:03,014 --> 00:28:04,983
Did you eat it often
when you studied abroad?

740
00:28:05,050 --> 00:28:07,185
I had it every night,

741
00:28:07,252 --> 00:28:09,254
at least once a day to quench my hunger.

742
00:28:09,320 --> 00:28:11,322
I owe half of my size

743
00:28:11,389 --> 00:28:13,858
to udon, and the other half to ramen.

744
00:28:13,925 --> 00:28:17,595
-You've had it that much?
-He's half-udon, half-ramen.

745
00:28:17,662 --> 00:28:20,632
You two have teamed up
in the past and lost.

746
00:28:20,699 --> 00:28:22,634
<i>Ever since you split up,</i>

747
00:28:22,701 --> 00:28:25,670
Ho-young has lost twice in a row,

748
00:28:25,737 --> 00:28:30,041
-whereas Sam has won twice.
-You're right.

749
00:28:30,108 --> 00:28:31,743
Is there a secret?

750
00:28:31,810 --> 00:28:33,445
I truly do try very hard.

751
00:28:33,511 --> 00:28:34,879
And I don't?

752
00:28:34,946 --> 00:28:37,716
Well, you do try hard.

753
00:28:37,782 --> 00:28:39,084
I guess you need to think a lot.

754
00:28:39,150 --> 00:28:42,420
-I don't?
-He tried hard without thinking much?

755
00:28:42,487 --> 00:28:44,656
Sam has never said
anything like that before.

756
00:28:44,723 --> 00:28:46,391
He's become quite feisty.

757
00:28:46,458 --> 00:28:48,326
He has. His words are harsher.

758
00:28:48,393 --> 00:28:50,295
These mind games are crazy.

759
00:28:50,361 --> 00:28:52,464
Ho-young doesn't look so pleased.

760
00:28:52,530 --> 00:28:56,367
I think it was luck
more than his actual ability.

761
00:28:56,868 --> 00:28:58,570
THE DISSES WON'T END

762
00:28:58,636 --> 00:29:00,638
-And it ends today?
-That was brutal.

763
00:29:00,705 --> 00:29:02,774
Why don't you just
slap each other and get over it?

764
00:29:03,041 --> 00:29:04,476
SLAP AND SETTLE

765
00:29:04,542 --> 00:29:06,878
It'll look bad if you use your hands,
so let's use noodles.

766
00:29:07,579 --> 00:29:10,281
Slap each other once with noodles
and end it there.

767
00:29:10,348 --> 00:29:12,283
I'm making ramen,
which isn't my specialty,

768
00:29:12,350 --> 00:29:15,220
but I will still show him
why I have twice as many stars.

769
00:29:15,520 --> 00:29:16,788
LOOK AT HIS SPIRIT

770
00:29:16,855 --> 00:29:18,123
-Bam.
-Hey, Sam.

771
00:29:18,189 --> 00:29:20,125
-He's done joking.
-His words.

772
00:29:20,191 --> 00:29:21,926
His spirit isn't what it was before.

773
00:29:21,993 --> 00:29:25,029
-Don't his canines look longer?
-Yes, they've become longer.

774
00:29:25,096 --> 00:29:28,833
I can even see that he's gotten
more plaque on his tooth.

775
00:29:28,900 --> 00:29:30,468
In this round,

776
00:29:30,535 --> 00:29:34,672
Jun-young will try to overcome
his introverted personality

777
00:29:34,739 --> 00:29:38,143
-by doing the five-minute interim check.
-Really?

778
00:29:38,209 --> 00:29:40,912
If he really wants
to break out of his shell,

779
00:29:40,979 --> 00:29:42,147
he should do it alone.

780
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:44,182
GASP!

781
00:29:44,249 --> 00:29:45,517
-Alone.
-Oh, no.

782
00:29:45,583 --> 00:29:46,551
Please help.

783
00:29:46,618 --> 00:29:48,653
-"Please help."
-He needs help.

784
00:29:48,887 --> 00:29:50,555
WHIMPERING

785
00:29:50,622 --> 00:29:52,357
-I'm not even your teacher.
-Listen to him.

786
00:29:52,423 --> 00:29:55,093
-He's so desperate.
-Please help him.

787
00:29:55,160 --> 00:29:57,929
I'm sure Jung-hwan will
lift away his introversion.

788
00:29:58,763 --> 00:30:00,832
CHEF HO-YOUNG'S INGREDIENTS:
RAMEN NOODLES, WHOLE CHICKEN, CHICKEN FEET

789
00:30:00,899 --> 00:30:02,934
PORK BELLY, DRIED SCALLOP,
DRIED CLAM MEAT, BONITO FLAKES, AND MORE

790
00:30:03,001 --> 00:30:05,003
Chef Ho-young, what are you making?

791
00:30:05,069 --> 00:30:07,972
Sam thinks I'm an easy fight,

792
00:30:08,039 --> 00:30:11,142
but when it comes to ramen,
it's something I've had so much.

793
00:30:11,209 --> 00:30:15,213
My wife once got furious at me
because I secretly simmered ramen broth

794
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:17,982
in a corner of my udon kitchen.

795
00:30:18,049 --> 00:30:21,519
-He almost got kicked out.
-So I've made ramen very often.

796
00:30:21,586 --> 00:30:25,156
But it's not easy to make in 15 minutes,

797
00:30:25,223 --> 00:30:28,526
so I'll share the ways

798
00:30:28,593 --> 00:30:30,762
you can simplify the recipe
yet make it taste good.

799
00:30:30,829 --> 00:30:33,665
-I'll do that for you.
-Thank you.

800
00:30:34,499 --> 00:30:36,568
CHEF SAM'S INGREDIENTS:
RAMEN NOODLES, WHOLE CHICKEN, CHICKEN FEET

801
00:30:36,634 --> 00:30:38,703
GUANCIALE, BUTTON MUSHROOM, BASIL,
OLIVE OIL, PECORINO, PARMESAN, AND MORE

802
00:30:38,770 --> 00:30:41,940
Sam, you're up against Ho-young.
What are you making?

803
00:30:43,474 --> 00:30:44,409
The dish

804
00:30:44,909 --> 00:30:46,344
I'll be making today is this.

805
00:30:46,411 --> 00:30:48,479
Instead of ordinary ramen,

806
00:30:48,546 --> 00:30:51,049
<i>-I want to make use of your herbs…</i>
<i>-Herbs.</i>

807
00:30:51,115 --> 00:30:55,153
<i>…</i>to make ramen
that an Italian would create.

808
00:30:55,220 --> 00:30:57,856
So I'll make ramen with basil pesto.

809
00:30:57,922 --> 00:30:59,057
-That's pasta.
-That's pasta.

810
00:30:59,123 --> 00:31:00,391
No.

811
00:31:00,458 --> 00:31:02,327
I'm using chicken broth.

812
00:31:02,393 --> 00:31:03,528
It's pasta with broth.

813
00:31:03,595 --> 00:31:05,396
It's pasta.

814
00:31:05,463 --> 00:31:06,598
Wait, no. It's ramen.

815
00:31:07,966 --> 00:31:09,434
-He's making a soup pasta.
-It's ramen.

816
00:31:10,034 --> 00:31:11,970
-I'll make ramen.
-Don't get them confused.

817
00:31:12,036 --> 00:31:14,038
There's something I'll use as garnish

818
00:31:14,105 --> 00:31:15,740
called gremolata.

819
00:31:15,807 --> 00:31:19,510
It's made with parsley, lemon,
and even some anchovies.

820
00:31:19,577 --> 00:31:21,846
That's going to add some savory flavor

821
00:31:21,913 --> 00:31:23,715
-into the dish.
-It sounds like anchovy pasta.

822
00:31:23,781 --> 00:31:26,150
I'll make ramen
you've probably never had before.

823
00:31:26,217 --> 00:31:27,585
SAM KIM'S UNIQUE 15-MINUTE RAMEN

824
00:31:27,652 --> 00:31:29,020
That sounds great. All right, then.

825
00:31:29,087 --> 00:31:33,591
Let us begin the round
When Life Hooks You on Ramen.

826
00:31:33,658 --> 00:31:35,860
Chef Jung Ho-young is here today

827
00:31:35,927 --> 00:31:39,497
not as the Udon Prince,
but the Ramen Prince.

828
00:31:39,564 --> 00:31:42,066
Up against him is Chef Sam Kim,

829
00:31:42,133 --> 00:31:44,936
who'll use his canine to burst

830
00:31:45,003 --> 00:31:47,839
his ramen sack through this cook-off.

831
00:31:47,906 --> 00:31:48,840
Chomp.

832
00:31:48,907 --> 00:31:52,310
The besties who have become enemies!
Who'll rise as the winner?

833
00:31:52,377 --> 00:31:54,946
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

834
00:31:55,947 --> 00:31:57,282
Good luck.

835
00:31:57,649 --> 00:31:59,617
SAM & HO'S FRIENDLY ROUND BEGINS!

836
00:31:59,684 --> 00:32:00,952
The chicken.

837
00:32:01,019 --> 00:32:02,120
Ho-young, the chicken.

838
00:32:02,186 --> 00:32:04,689
We have to share the chicken.

839
00:32:05,223 --> 00:32:07,225
HO-YOUNG BEGINS BY PREPPING THE CHICKEN

840
00:32:07,525 --> 00:32:08,626
WHILE HE SPLITS THE CHICKEN,

841
00:32:08,826 --> 00:32:09,694
SAM GETS STARTED FIRST!

842
00:32:09,761 --> 00:32:11,095
-Chicken feet?
-Chicken feet?

843
00:32:11,162 --> 00:32:12,463
Chicken feet.

844
00:32:12,530 --> 00:32:13,464
DONE WITH THE CHICKEN

845
00:32:13,531 --> 00:32:15,199
-Half a chicken.
-Half a chicken.

846
00:32:15,266 --> 00:32:16,334
He put it in for him.

847
00:32:16,401 --> 00:32:17,568
Put it in there. Thanks.

848
00:32:17,635 --> 00:32:18,736
Is that pancetta?

849
00:32:18,803 --> 00:32:21,205
-It's guanciale.
-Guanciale?

850
00:32:21,272 --> 00:32:23,441
-He didn't put the leg in.
-Why not?

851
00:32:23,508 --> 00:32:24,842
-Why is it out?
-Why is the leg out?

852
00:32:24,909 --> 00:32:27,211
Sam, the drumstick is sticking out.

853
00:32:27,445 --> 00:32:28,379
CHUCKLING

854
00:32:28,446 --> 00:32:30,615
Let it rest out here.

855
00:32:32,116 --> 00:32:34,218
Dang it. Cut it out.

856
00:32:34,285 --> 00:32:35,687
BANTERING FIERCELY FROM THE START

857
00:32:35,753 --> 00:32:38,556
It looks like
they're making broth with chicken.

858
00:32:39,424 --> 00:32:40,825
Mushroom.

859
00:32:40,892 --> 00:32:43,161
-Mushroom.
-Mushroom. Hurry.

860
00:32:43,227 --> 00:32:45,430
Chicken broth. He's making broth.

861
00:32:45,496 --> 00:32:47,131
-Right now…
-It'll take a while.

862
00:32:47,198 --> 00:32:49,701
They're both using
chicken and chicken feet.

863
00:32:49,767 --> 00:32:52,437
Which side will make the broth faster?

864
00:32:52,503 --> 00:32:54,839
A PRESSURE COOKER!

865
00:32:54,906 --> 00:32:56,674
They have so many ingredients
to work with.

866
00:32:56,741 --> 00:33:00,111
-Hey. What's that?
-He poured oil over bonito flakes.

867
00:33:00,178 --> 00:33:01,312
BONITO FLAKES AND COOKING OIL?

868
00:33:01,379 --> 00:33:04,716
Pour a bit of oil over this
and microwave it for a minute.

869
00:33:04,782 --> 00:33:05,683
But why?

870
00:33:05,750 --> 00:33:09,187
This way, you can bring out the umami
without making the bonito broth.

871
00:33:09,253 --> 00:33:10,755
A SECRET TO A QUICK UMAMI FIX!

872
00:33:10,822 --> 00:33:13,658
As we expected, he knows
all the secrets to Japanese cooking.

873
00:33:14,459 --> 00:33:16,661
SKILLFULLY CUTTING THIN SLICES!

874
00:33:17,795 --> 00:33:18,997
HE'S USING A WOK, NOT A PAN?

875
00:33:19,063 --> 00:33:20,198
You're cooking them?

876
00:33:20,264 --> 00:33:22,700
-I'm making <i>chashu.</i>
<i>-Chashu?</i>

877
00:33:22,934 --> 00:33:24,302
POURING

878
00:33:24,369 --> 00:33:27,438
You're using that much cooking wine?
Won't that make it too sweet?

879
00:33:27,505 --> 00:33:28,606
-It's okay.
-He's boiling it.

880
00:33:28,673 --> 00:33:31,976
He cooks it in cooking wine
because it makes the meat tender quickly.

881
00:33:32,043 --> 00:33:34,145
I see. To tenderize the meat.

882
00:33:34,445 --> 00:33:36,180
WHAT ABOUT THE ITALIAN CHEF'S RAMEN?

883
00:33:36,247 --> 00:33:38,282
-Olive oil.
-He adds olive oil.

884
00:33:38,349 --> 00:33:40,885
-I'm making basil pesto.
-Garlic and cheese.

885
00:33:40,952 --> 00:33:42,453
He's making basil pesto.

886
00:33:42,520 --> 00:33:45,156
3. GRIND BASIL, OLIVE OIL, GARLIC,
PECORINO, AND ADD PARMESAN

887
00:33:45,223 --> 00:33:49,660
Actually, chicken-based ramen
tastes great with pesto on the side.

888
00:33:49,727 --> 00:33:51,262
-Really?
-And such ramen exists.

889
00:33:51,329 --> 00:33:52,864
-Is that really a thing?
-Yes.

890
00:33:52,930 --> 00:33:54,432
They do go well together.

891
00:33:54,499 --> 00:33:56,267
-That's your mortar, right?
-Yes.

892
00:33:56,334 --> 00:33:59,904
He also said
this was his favorite olive oil.

893
00:33:59,971 --> 00:34:02,273
How do you usually use the mortar?

894
00:34:02,340 --> 00:34:04,142
I usually roast spices

895
00:34:04,208 --> 00:34:06,677
and use that to crush them.

896
00:34:06,744 --> 00:34:07,578
PHEW

897
00:34:08,813 --> 00:34:09,881
-Shallots?
-Shallots?

898
00:34:09,947 --> 00:34:11,549
-Shallots.
-He had shallots?

899
00:34:11,616 --> 00:34:13,284
He has lots of ingredients to work with.

900
00:34:13,351 --> 00:34:14,685
He's deep-frying something.

901
00:34:14,752 --> 00:34:16,854
-Shallots.
-Shallots? I see.

902
00:34:16,921 --> 00:34:17,955
For ramen?

903
00:34:18,022 --> 00:34:19,290
It's been three minutes.

904
00:34:19,357 --> 00:34:22,326
Whose broth will finish faster?

905
00:34:22,393 --> 00:34:24,128
Japanese chef versus Italian chef.

906
00:34:24,195 --> 00:34:25,696
15-MINUTE EGGS! SET TO 6 MIN. 30 SEC.!

907
00:34:26,264 --> 00:34:28,166
AND 15-MINUTE CHASHU

908
00:34:28,399 --> 00:34:30,168
3. BOIL PORK IN COOKING WINE,
ADD WATER, GARLIC, SOY SAUCE

909
00:34:30,234 --> 00:34:32,837
You can see that he studied in Japan.

910
00:34:32,904 --> 00:34:33,771
BONITO FLAKES, 1 MINUTE!

911
00:34:33,838 --> 00:34:35,440
Is it done?

912
00:34:35,506 --> 00:34:37,308
-That's done already?
-Whoa.

913
00:34:37,375 --> 00:34:38,242
I can smell it.

914
00:34:38,309 --> 00:34:40,545
The bonito flakes smell really strong.

915
00:34:40,611 --> 00:34:41,979
Yes, it's very strong.

916
00:34:42,046 --> 00:34:44,916
When you don't have enough time,
you can microwave it.

917
00:34:45,616 --> 00:34:46,784
KELP SOAKED IN WATER

918
00:34:47,018 --> 00:34:48,319
HE SCOOPS UP THE WATER?

919
00:34:48,386 --> 00:34:49,220
DRIED CLAM-INFUSED WATER

920
00:34:49,287 --> 00:34:52,090
I'll use the kelp soaking water

921
00:34:52,156 --> 00:34:53,758
to beat the egg white with it.

922
00:34:53,825 --> 00:34:54,826
To make meringue?

923
00:34:54,892 --> 00:34:56,727
-Meringue.
-Why? Why meringue?

924
00:34:56,794 --> 00:34:58,963
You're making meringue for ramen?

925
00:34:59,030 --> 00:35:00,531
It doesn't touch the mixture.

926
00:35:00,598 --> 00:35:02,266
-It's supposed to spin.
-It is.

927
00:35:02,600 --> 00:35:04,102
NAM-NO TO THE RESCUE

928
00:35:05,069 --> 00:35:07,271
He rarely needs meringue,
so he doesn't know.

929
00:35:07,338 --> 00:35:08,806
It's the bowl.

930
00:35:08,873 --> 00:35:11,109
I don't think the top is shut all the way.

931
00:35:11,175 --> 00:35:12,844
The top. That's it.

932
00:35:12,910 --> 00:35:14,946
I'm beating the egg

933
00:35:15,012 --> 00:35:18,416
with kelp-infused water,
which will increase the flavor

934
00:35:18,483 --> 00:35:20,151
when it meets bonito.

935
00:35:20,218 --> 00:35:22,320
-I'm curious.
-Whoa. That's new.

936
00:35:22,386 --> 00:35:25,189
I'll let it lean here like this.

937
00:35:25,590 --> 00:35:26,724
WHAT'S SAM'S KICK?

938
00:35:26,791 --> 00:35:28,626
-Rosemary?
-Rosemary?

939
00:35:28,693 --> 00:35:30,027
-You're using rosemary too?
-Yes.

940
00:35:30,094 --> 00:35:31,429
You had rosemary?

941
00:35:31,496 --> 00:35:34,232
Rosemary? That herb smells really strong.

942
00:35:34,298 --> 00:35:36,767
-It is strong. They're both strong.
-And Parsley?

943
00:35:36,834 --> 00:35:39,070
-Parsley.
-Will it go well with ramen?

944
00:35:39,137 --> 00:35:41,405
-Are you making curry?
-Looks like it.

945
00:35:41,472 --> 00:35:42,607
You are making ramen, right?

946
00:35:42,673 --> 00:35:44,208
Yes, I'm making ramen.

947
00:35:44,275 --> 00:35:46,978
-He's using a lot of herbs.
-What are those for?

948
00:35:47,044 --> 00:35:48,646
Don't try to call it cold ramen

949
00:35:48,713 --> 00:35:50,047
-after making pasta.
-I won't.

950
00:35:50,114 --> 00:35:52,483
-Olive oil.
-Hey, you know…

951
00:35:52,550 --> 00:35:55,253
Doesn't it seem like he's making pasta
with all those ingredients?

952
00:35:55,319 --> 00:35:57,188
He's marinating the chicken.

953
00:35:57,255 --> 00:35:59,223
Whoa. This is all so cool.

954
00:35:59,490 --> 00:36:00,324
PEEKING

955
00:36:00,391 --> 00:36:02,393
Don't forget about the shallots.

956
00:36:02,460 --> 00:36:03,928
-Shallots!
-Whoa!

957
00:36:03,995 --> 00:36:05,463
For ramen?

958
00:36:06,497 --> 00:36:08,599
-Is that a garnish?
-Yes.

959
00:36:08,666 --> 00:36:11,469
You have nine minutes left.

960
00:36:11,536 --> 00:36:14,071
Everything just…

961
00:36:14,138 --> 00:36:17,175
-Time flies, doesn't it?
-I feel so bad.

962
00:36:17,608 --> 00:36:19,477
THE TIMER FOR THE SOFT-BOILED EGGS

963
00:36:19,544 --> 00:36:22,346
Cook eggs in boiling water
for 6 minutes and 30 seconds.

964
00:36:22,413 --> 00:36:26,050
Then dilute your <i>tsuyu</i> with some water

965
00:36:26,117 --> 00:36:29,287
-and turn the heat off when it boils.
-That's it?

966
00:36:29,353 --> 00:36:31,622
You usually need bonito powder or flakes,

967
00:36:31,689 --> 00:36:34,625
but you can easily switch it out
with <i>tsuyu</i>.

968
00:36:36,027 --> 00:36:38,095
Wait, it's burning.

969
00:36:38,162 --> 00:36:40,097
Wait, it's burning.

970
00:36:40,598 --> 00:36:42,166
THE GUANCIALE FACES A CRISIS!

971
00:36:42,233 --> 00:36:44,135
-It burned!
-It's not burnt.

972
00:36:44,835 --> 00:36:46,537
AN EMERGENCY

973
00:36:46,604 --> 00:36:48,272
-It's burnt!
-It's not.

974
00:36:48,339 --> 00:36:49,574
-It's burnt!
-It's charred.

975
00:36:49,640 --> 00:36:51,175
It's charred?

976
00:36:51,242 --> 00:36:52,777
-Charred?
-Sung-jun, grab this.

977
00:36:52,843 --> 00:36:55,746
-No, that's burnt.
-Is it that thing?

978
00:36:55,813 --> 00:36:59,116
It looks like that seaweed snack.

979
00:36:59,183 --> 00:37:01,452
It looks like my childhood snack,
fried grasshoppers.

980
00:37:01,519 --> 00:37:04,488
Ho-young is done with the meringue.

981
00:37:04,855 --> 00:37:07,658
GETTING CURIOUS ABOUT KELP MERINGUE

982
00:37:08,626 --> 00:37:10,261
It's… Oh, it's over ice.

983
00:37:11,562 --> 00:37:12,763
You'll have to go check them soon.

984
00:37:13,231 --> 00:37:15,866
I'M FEELING YOU

985
00:37:15,933 --> 00:37:18,002
Only two minutes
until the five-minute check!

986
00:37:18,236 --> 00:37:19,170
SIGH…

987
00:37:19,237 --> 00:37:20,404
His hands are getting clammy!

988
00:37:20,638 --> 00:37:21,706
CLAMMY HANDS

989
00:37:21,772 --> 00:37:23,841
DRY MOUTH

990
00:37:23,908 --> 00:37:25,376
Parsley.

991
00:37:25,443 --> 00:37:26,344
SAM TEARS MORE GREENS INTO PIECES

992
00:37:26,410 --> 00:37:29,213
We're seeing lots of ingredients
for Western cuisine.

993
00:37:29,280 --> 00:37:31,282
Italian parsley and even lemon.

994
00:37:31,349 --> 00:37:34,952
-That's Western cuisine.
-He's just making pasta.

995
00:37:35,019 --> 00:37:37,455
Will he insist that it's ramen
after making pasta?

996
00:37:37,521 --> 00:37:40,124
-First, he'll make pasta.
-That's not ramen.

997
00:37:40,191 --> 00:37:41,525
It's overflowing!

998
00:37:41,592 --> 00:37:42,727
IT'S OVERFLOWINGINGNG%#$!

999
00:37:42,793 --> 00:37:44,028
You used too much water!

1000
00:37:44,095 --> 00:37:45,830
It always overflows when you use too much!

1001
00:37:45,896 --> 00:37:47,698
How many times have I told you?

1002
00:37:47,765 --> 00:37:49,934
His ramen seems
very different from Ho-young's.

1003
00:37:50,167 --> 00:37:52,470
HERB CHICKEN CHASHU!

1004
00:37:53,037 --> 00:37:54,338
Chef Sam released

1005
00:37:54,405 --> 00:37:56,107
the pressure valve first.

1006
00:37:56,173 --> 00:38:00,044
-Ho-young's broth may be a bit richer.
-I see.

1007
00:38:00,111 --> 00:38:02,013
-Six minutes!
-Hurry.

1008
00:38:02,079 --> 00:38:04,448
-Sam, are you opening it already?
-I am.

1009
00:38:04,515 --> 00:38:06,117
Isn't it too early?

1010
00:38:06,183 --> 00:38:08,953
-Give it some more time.
-Look! Too much water!

1011
00:38:09,020 --> 00:38:10,288
My goodness.

1012
00:38:11,255 --> 00:38:13,257
-The same happens to Ho-young.
-It's a hot spring.

1013
00:38:13,324 --> 00:38:14,659
A hot spring.

1014
00:38:14,725 --> 00:38:18,529
-The hot spring surges.
-I told you not to use too much water!

1015
00:38:18,596 --> 00:38:20,131
It's boiling over!

1016
00:38:20,197 --> 00:38:21,632
Ho-young begins to cook noodles.

1017
00:38:22,833 --> 00:38:24,435
Why do you have to stir?

1018
00:38:24,502 --> 00:38:25,736
Otherwise, they'll stick to each other.

1019
00:38:25,803 --> 00:38:27,338
-Get entangled?
-You have to separate them.

1020
00:38:27,605 --> 00:38:28,539
SEASONED EGGS, DONE

1021
00:38:28,606 --> 00:38:31,942
-That's new.
-Look at the color.

1022
00:38:32,576 --> 00:38:33,411
THE EGGS TOOK LESS THAN 10 MINUTES!

1023
00:38:33,477 --> 00:38:36,380
The eggs will absorb the sauce faster
as it cools.

1024
00:38:36,447 --> 00:38:38,215
I knew it.

1025
00:38:38,282 --> 00:38:39,650
-Five minutes!
-Okay!

1026
00:38:39,717 --> 00:38:41,719
-Jun-young!
-Jung-hwan and Jun-young!

1027
00:38:41,786 --> 00:38:45,356
-Please do the five-minute check!
-Grab the spoons, and let's go!

1028
00:38:45,623 --> 00:38:46,924
IT'S AS IF HE'S ARRESTED

1029
00:38:46,991 --> 00:38:50,728
Which one will capture
Jun-young's taste for ramen?

1030
00:38:50,795 --> 00:38:52,229
This needs to depressurize soon.

1031
00:38:52,296 --> 00:38:55,466
-It's taking forever to depressurize.
-Use cold water!

1032
00:38:55,533 --> 00:38:58,569
Pour cold water over it.

1033
00:38:58,636 --> 00:39:01,972
-I hope that broth turns out nicely.
-Yes.

1034
00:39:03,007 --> 00:39:04,875
Jun-young hides in the back.

1035
00:39:04,942 --> 00:39:07,878
-You're cooking chicken, right?
-That's right.

1036
00:39:07,945 --> 00:39:10,281
-Would you like to taste some raw chicken?
-No, thanks.

1037
00:39:10,348 --> 00:39:14,385
Ho-young knows a few things
when it comes to ramen.

1038
00:39:14,452 --> 00:39:17,088
So you're making <i>chashu</i>
by boiling it down in the sauce.

1039
00:39:17,154 --> 00:39:19,123
I'll sear it with a torch too.

1040
00:39:19,190 --> 00:39:20,891
With a torch? I see.

1041
00:39:21,425 --> 00:39:22,727
AND THE COOLED PRESSURE COOKER?

1042
00:39:22,793 --> 00:39:24,028
It'll probably open now. Okay.

1043
00:39:24,095 --> 00:39:25,596
SUCCESSFULLY OPENED!

1044
00:39:26,397 --> 00:39:27,832
That broth is ready, Jung-hwan!

1045
00:39:27,898 --> 00:39:29,900
-Sam's broth is ready!
-The broth!

1046
00:39:29,967 --> 00:39:31,902
-Try the broth!
-You should try the broth!

1047
00:39:31,969 --> 00:39:35,306
-The broth!
-Do you like this kind of broth for ramen?

1048
00:39:35,373 --> 00:39:36,440
Try the soup!

1049
00:39:37,808 --> 00:39:40,077
Does it taste like
it's been simmered for 48 hours?

1050
00:39:41,612 --> 00:39:44,582
ALL ATTENTION ON HIM
WHAT WILL THE EXTREME INTROVERT SAY?

1051
00:39:44,648 --> 00:39:45,783
YOU CAN RISE ABOVE THIS!

1052
00:39:48,352 --> 00:39:49,420
Yes, it does!

1053
00:39:50,421 --> 00:39:51,288
Yes, it does!

1054
00:39:51,355 --> 00:39:52,990
HE DID IT!

1055
00:39:53,391 --> 00:39:54,892
GREAT JOB!

1056
00:39:54,959 --> 00:39:56,293
For 48 hours?

1057
00:39:56,360 --> 00:39:57,828
PEOPLE OF EARTH, I NEED YOUR POWER!

1058
00:39:57,895 --> 00:40:00,598
SHOOTING OUT HIS ENERGY!

1059
00:40:01,098 --> 00:40:02,566
SOBBING

1060
00:40:02,633 --> 00:40:04,535
He took a minute to respond.

1061
00:40:05,569 --> 00:40:07,338
-"Yes, it does!"
-"Yes, it does!"

1062
00:40:07,405 --> 00:40:08,939
YOU DID IT, LEE JUN-YOUNG

1063
00:40:09,774 --> 00:40:10,975
You have to cook the noodles.

1064
00:40:11,041 --> 00:40:12,376
The noodles.

1065
00:40:12,610 --> 00:40:14,111
SAM BEGINS TO COOK THE NOODLES!

1066
00:40:14,378 --> 00:40:16,580
HO-YOUNG FINISHES COOKING THE NOODLES!

1067
00:40:16,647 --> 00:40:18,449
SHAKING OFF POWERFULLY!

1068
00:40:18,516 --> 00:40:19,650
MAKE SOME NOISE!

1069
00:40:20,551 --> 00:40:24,054
THE RAMEN EXPERT
SHAKES IT OFF WITH HIS POWER!

1070
00:40:30,294 --> 00:40:31,529
That was too over the top.

1071
00:40:31,595 --> 00:40:35,166
-He timed the noodles accurately.
-It was 2 minutes and 30 seconds.

1072
00:40:35,232 --> 00:40:37,067
Are you allowed to rinse it in cold water?

1073
00:40:37,134 --> 00:40:38,502
You can do that.

1074
00:40:38,569 --> 00:40:41,806
-Ho-young's broth is ready too. It's done.
-Ho-young's.

1075
00:40:41,872 --> 00:40:44,642
That broth is everything.

1076
00:40:44,708 --> 00:40:46,844
-What will it be like?
-What is this?

1077
00:40:46,911 --> 00:40:48,145
-Fire.
-What fire?

1078
00:40:48,212 --> 00:40:50,381
-The blowtorch.
-The torch? The torch.

1079
00:40:50,448 --> 00:40:52,483
-The torch.
-The torch.

1080
00:40:52,550 --> 00:40:55,186
-Two minutes and thirty seconds!
-What's Ho-young's soup like?

1081
00:40:55,252 --> 00:40:57,321
-Two minutes and thirty seconds!
-What's Ho-young's soup like?

1082
00:40:57,388 --> 00:40:58,756
I just added some love.

1083
00:40:58,823 --> 00:41:00,257
I threw in some love.

1084
00:41:00,324 --> 00:41:01,892
-What's Ho-young's soup like?
-The soup!

1085
00:41:02,660 --> 00:41:04,428
This is fantastic.

1086
00:41:04,495 --> 00:41:06,664
He mumbled to himself,
"This is fantastic."

1087
00:41:06,997 --> 00:41:08,466
I'M CURIOUS

1088
00:41:09,667 --> 00:41:10,968
I didn't open the lid.

1089
00:41:11,235 --> 00:41:13,270
HEY! YOU DID THAT TOO?

1090
00:41:13,504 --> 00:41:14,839
6. SEASON WITH LOVE AND SOY SAUCE

1091
00:41:14,905 --> 00:41:17,274
Is it better than the broth
you simmered for 48 hours?

1092
00:41:18,108 --> 00:41:19,777
I did all that for nothing!

1093
00:41:19,844 --> 00:41:20,778
HEHEHE

1094
00:41:20,845 --> 00:41:23,681
-He did it all for nothing!
-He wasted all those 48 hours!

1095
00:41:23,747 --> 00:41:24,949
Two minutes left!

1096
00:41:25,015 --> 00:41:28,052
-A minute and 50 seconds!
-Hurry up!

1097
00:41:28,118 --> 00:41:29,453
TRULY AMAZED

1098
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:31,655
-You have to sear the <i>chashu.</i>
<i>-Chashu.</i>

1099
00:41:31,722 --> 00:41:34,024
You have to sear the <i>chashu</i>.

1100
00:41:34,091 --> 00:41:36,460
7. SEAR BRAISED PORK BELLY CHASHU
OVER A GRIDIRON

1101
00:41:36,794 --> 00:41:38,729
FIGHTS HIM WITH HERB CHICKEN CHASHU

1102
00:41:39,029 --> 00:41:43,601
9. FLATTEN PRECOOKED CHICKEN
AND BROIL ON A GRIDIRON

1103
00:41:44,168 --> 00:41:45,469
ALSO SEARING!

1104
00:41:45,936 --> 00:41:47,872
PUTS GREMOLATA IN A BOWL

1105
00:41:48,272 --> 00:41:50,608
AND GRABS AN ANCHOVY

1106
00:41:51,108 --> 00:41:53,511
TOP GREMOLATA
WITH ANCHOVY AND A LEMON WEDGE

1107
00:41:53,577 --> 00:41:55,346
ANCHOVY GREMOLATA

1108
00:41:56,247 --> 00:41:57,348
He's searing the meat too!

1109
00:41:57,414 --> 00:41:59,216
-I knew it.
-Looks great.

1110
00:42:00,084 --> 00:42:02,653
TIME TO PLATE THE NOODLES!

1111
00:42:02,987 --> 00:42:04,488
MARINATED EGG

1112
00:42:04,555 --> 00:42:07,525
I thought Sam was making pasta,

1113
00:42:07,591 --> 00:42:09,727
but he made proper broth.

1114
00:42:09,793 --> 00:42:11,929
Wait, is the chicken cooked?

1115
00:42:11,996 --> 00:42:12,997
Yeah, yeah.

1116
00:42:13,564 --> 00:42:15,099
-"Yeah, yeah"?
-Yes.

1117
00:42:15,699 --> 00:42:17,301
THE FORMER ATHLETE IS ALL ABOUT DISCIPLINE

1118
00:42:17,368 --> 00:42:19,270
I asked you politely, and you said,

1119
00:42:19,336 --> 00:42:20,738
"Yeah, yeah"?

1120
00:42:20,804 --> 00:42:23,707
-He's pouring broth over the noodles.
-Right now?

1121
00:42:23,941 --> 00:42:25,576
WHOA

1122
00:42:26,176 --> 00:42:27,444
The broth is clear.

1123
00:42:27,511 --> 00:42:28,345
-That's ramen.
-It is.

1124
00:42:28,412 --> 00:42:30,347
-Not bad.
-It is ramen. One minute.

1125
00:42:30,414 --> 00:42:33,150
-And the grilled chicken goes on top.
-It's hot.

1126
00:42:33,217 --> 00:42:35,486
Shallot rings on ramen?

1127
00:42:35,553 --> 00:42:37,788
You got this! Shout it out loud.

1128
00:42:37,855 --> 00:42:39,256
Why don't we shout it together?

1129
00:42:39,323 --> 00:42:40,291
You got this, chefs!

1130
00:42:40,357 --> 00:42:41,992
-You got this, chefs!
-You got this!

1131
00:42:42,393 --> 00:42:44,061
THE BIGGEST SUPPORT FROM THE INTROVERT

1132
00:42:44,128 --> 00:42:46,497
You got this!

1133
00:42:46,564 --> 00:42:47,965
-<i>Chashu!</i>
-There's the <i>chashu!</i>

1134
00:42:48,699 --> 00:42:49,533
SAM FINISHES FIRST!

1135
00:42:49,733 --> 00:42:51,702
TAKES THE ADVANTAGE IN THE NOODLES ROUND!

1136
00:42:51,969 --> 00:42:53,304
THE GENERAL MANAGER IS EXCITED

1137
00:42:53,370 --> 00:42:55,406
BUT ASSISTANT MANAGER PARK IS JUST TIRED

1138
00:42:55,673 --> 00:42:56,774
THE ROOKIE GOT CAUGHT

1139
00:42:56,840 --> 00:42:58,375
-Ho-young's almost done too.
-Fifteen.

1140
00:42:58,442 --> 00:43:01,178
-You don't have much time left.
-He's almost done.

1141
00:43:01,245 --> 00:43:02,813
-Twelve!
-Twelve!

1142
00:43:02,880 --> 00:43:04,148
Jun-young, count down with us.

1143
00:43:04,415 --> 00:43:06,383
THE KELP MERINGUE!

1144
00:43:06,450 --> 00:43:08,285
-Seven. Six.
-Seven. Six.

1145
00:43:08,352 --> 00:43:10,287
SPECIAL MERINGUE RAMEN

1146
00:43:10,354 --> 00:43:12,122
-Three. Two.
-Three. Two.

1147
00:43:12,189 --> 00:43:13,424
-One.
-One.

1148
00:43:13,490 --> 00:43:15,392
-Time's up!
-Time's up!

1149
00:43:15,459 --> 00:43:17,328
-Whoa, that goes on top?
-Ho-young's done.

1150
00:43:17,394 --> 00:43:18,228
The meringue.

1151
00:43:18,295 --> 00:43:20,331
Ho-young finishes too.

1152
00:43:20,397 --> 00:43:23,233
Can you shout out,
"And now, they're both done cooking"?

1153
00:43:23,300 --> 00:43:24,501
And now,

1154
00:43:24,568 --> 00:43:26,337
they're both done cooking!

1155
00:43:26,403 --> 00:43:27,705
SO BRAVE

1156
00:43:28,138 --> 00:43:31,875
15-MINUTE RAMEN!
THEY MADE IT HAPPEN YET AGAIN

1157
00:43:32,643 --> 00:43:33,677
Gosh.

1158
00:43:33,744 --> 00:43:34,845
-Thank you.
-Great job.

1159
00:43:34,912 --> 00:43:36,580
-Thank you.
-Good work.

1160
00:43:36,647 --> 00:43:38,716
That was funny. You did a great job.

1161
00:43:38,782 --> 00:43:40,684
-Great job.
-Thank you.

1162
00:43:41,185 --> 00:43:43,520
-You must feel flushed.
-My gosh.

1163
00:43:43,587 --> 00:43:45,255
You might fall ill after this.

1164
00:43:45,522 --> 00:43:46,824
YOU'VE DONE WELL, LEE JUN-YOUNG

1165
00:43:46,890 --> 00:43:50,995
Both bowls of ramen were finished
just for Jun-young!

1166
00:43:52,630 --> 00:43:55,132
-You had to go do the interim check.
-Yes.

1167
00:43:55,199 --> 00:43:56,266
What was it like?

1168
00:43:56,333 --> 00:43:58,435
I'll be bedridden for a week too.

1169
00:43:59,670 --> 00:44:02,272
-It's a cruel place.
-But your favorite, ramen, awaits you.

1170
00:44:02,339 --> 00:44:06,010
After you tried the broth,
you said, "I did it all for nothing."

1171
00:44:06,744 --> 00:44:08,245
I did all that for nothing!

1172
00:44:08,312 --> 00:44:09,647
He did all that for nothing!

1173
00:44:10,214 --> 00:44:13,917
I've never used a pressure cooker,

1174
00:44:13,984 --> 00:44:17,121
so it never crossed my mind
that it'd make it so quickly.

1175
00:44:17,187 --> 00:44:18,856
They have such skills.

1176
00:44:18,922 --> 00:44:20,658
-He should try that quickly. It's ramen.
-Yes.

1177
00:44:20,724 --> 00:44:22,192
Please try Sam's dish first.

1178
00:44:22,259 --> 00:44:24,294
<i>Why Do You Only, Only Make Noodles?</i>

1179
00:44:24,361 --> 00:44:25,996
-<i>Hey!</i>
-Try that first.

1180
00:44:26,463 --> 00:44:29,133
ADDING AROMAS TO THE RAMEN,
BASIL PESTO AND GREMOLATA

1181
00:44:30,768 --> 00:44:33,604
CHICKEN BROTH TOPPED WITH CHICKEN CHASHU

1182
00:44:33,837 --> 00:44:35,739
How should he eat it?

1183
00:44:35,806 --> 00:44:38,676
Well, it was made only with chicken broth.

1184
00:44:38,742 --> 00:44:42,446
So on the very top, add some basil pesto.

1185
00:44:42,513 --> 00:44:47,618
And then, feel free to add some
parsley and lemon zest mix too.

1186
00:44:47,685 --> 00:44:50,954
He's as good as a ramen expert.

1187
00:44:51,522 --> 00:44:53,957
That ramen looks different.

1188
00:44:54,024 --> 00:44:55,859
-You should add lots of that.
-More?

1189
00:44:55,926 --> 00:44:57,094
Add lots of pesto.

1190
00:44:57,161 --> 00:44:59,163
-The more, the better.
-Like this?

1191
00:45:00,798 --> 00:45:01,732
ANOTHER SPOONFUL

1192
00:45:01,799 --> 00:45:03,967
-Can he add that much?
-Yes.

1193
00:45:04,034 --> 00:45:05,703
Even I can smell the chicken broth.

1194
00:45:05,769 --> 00:45:06,970
That smells so good.

1195
00:45:07,037 --> 00:45:08,238
-It does smell good.
-Yes.

1196
00:45:08,305 --> 00:45:09,573
But it's turning into pasta.

1197
00:45:09,640 --> 00:45:11,241
THE BROTH IS ABOUT TO DISAPPEAR

1198
00:45:11,308 --> 00:45:13,310
-Pasta with broth.
-Basil pasta with broth.

1199
00:45:13,377 --> 00:45:15,012
Did you add less broth on purpose?

1200
00:45:15,079 --> 00:45:17,014
I wanted him to try
the concentrated flavor.

1201
00:45:17,848 --> 00:45:20,584
EYES TURN SERIOUS

1202
00:45:20,651 --> 00:45:23,387
-Sam Kim-style ramen.
-His ramen.

1203
00:45:24,154 --> 00:45:26,356
A BIG FIRST BITE

1204
00:45:29,159 --> 00:45:31,562
The noodles are the ones he always eats.

1205
00:45:31,628 --> 00:45:33,731
-It looked nicely cooked.
-He's enjoying it a lot.

1206
00:45:33,797 --> 00:45:35,999
-Is it different? What's it like?
-He sounded amazed.

1207
00:45:37,034 --> 00:45:38,936
-He seems to like it.
-The noodles were cooked

1208
00:45:39,002 --> 00:45:40,537
perfectly to my preference.

1209
00:45:40,971 --> 00:45:42,506
RELIEVED

1210
00:45:43,273 --> 00:45:47,211
He must've had lots of ramen,
but never this kind.

1211
00:45:47,277 --> 00:45:48,645
He's devouring it.

1212
00:45:48,712 --> 00:45:52,416
I mean, that soup
is a mix of chicken broth and basil pesto.

1213
00:45:53,217 --> 00:45:54,351
MMM!

1214
00:45:54,418 --> 00:45:56,520
Is the chicken good? The chicken.

1215
00:45:56,587 --> 00:45:57,788
It's so good.

1216
00:45:58,021 --> 00:45:59,256
FEELING PROUD

1217
00:45:59,323 --> 00:46:00,390
This makes you

1218
00:46:00,457 --> 00:46:02,760
feel like you're eating pasta,

1219
00:46:02,826 --> 00:46:04,528
-but it's ramen.
-It's ramen.

1220
00:46:04,595 --> 00:46:07,965
I thought the basil pesto
wouldn't mix well with chicken broth.

1221
00:46:08,031 --> 00:46:09,333
They go so well together.

1222
00:46:09,399 --> 00:46:10,534
So well?

1223
00:46:10,601 --> 00:46:13,403
I don't particularly love basil pesto,

1224
00:46:13,470 --> 00:46:16,240
but that's about to shift right now.

1225
00:46:16,306 --> 00:46:18,008
It's so good.

1226
00:46:18,075 --> 00:46:19,877
-What do I do with this?
-Add the parsley?

1227
00:46:19,943 --> 00:46:24,014
You'll find an anchovy
and lemon zest in the parsley.

1228
00:46:24,081 --> 00:46:26,750
So if you mix that in,
you'll experience a different flavor.

1229
00:46:26,817 --> 00:46:30,387
I'm sure it'll change
once you add that in.

1230
00:46:30,454 --> 00:46:32,222
MIXING

1231
00:46:32,289 --> 00:46:34,224
He's tasting many different flavors.

1232
00:46:35,259 --> 00:46:36,160
That's just pasta.

1233
00:46:37,194 --> 00:46:38,796
YUM

1234
00:46:39,830 --> 00:46:40,664
He does.

1235
00:46:40,731 --> 00:46:42,800
-He eats so well.
-He does.

1236
00:46:42,866 --> 00:46:44,334
IMMERSED IN HIS RAMEN MUKBANG

1237
00:46:45,002 --> 00:46:45,836
MMM!

1238
00:46:45,903 --> 00:46:47,070
-Is it different?
-What is it?

1239
00:46:47,137 --> 00:46:48,639
WHAT IS IT?

1240
00:46:49,206 --> 00:46:50,874
This just turned it into pasta.

1241
00:46:52,876 --> 00:46:54,211
IN THE END, IT BECAME PASTA

1242
00:46:54,278 --> 00:46:57,047
The more sauce you add,
the more it'll turn into pasta.

1243
00:46:57,114 --> 00:47:00,484
That's why he said
even Italians would love it.

1244
00:47:00,551 --> 00:47:03,654
-They would love it so much.
-They would?

1245
00:47:04,421 --> 00:47:06,523
There is some soup.

1246
00:47:08,258 --> 00:47:10,160
-It's so delicious.
-It must be.

1247
00:47:10,227 --> 00:47:12,196
I want to try it too. It looks good.

1248
00:47:12,262 --> 00:47:14,565
It's quite shocking that he made this

1249
00:47:14,631 --> 00:47:17,267
in such a short time.

1250
00:47:17,334 --> 00:47:19,203
It was shocking for him.

1251
00:47:19,269 --> 00:47:21,171
Is there something you'd like to make?

1252
00:47:21,238 --> 00:47:23,740
This basil pesto is so delicious.

1253
00:47:24,875 --> 00:47:29,379
Also, it's always a huge trouble
when I make <i>chashu </i>with chicken.

1254
00:47:29,446 --> 00:47:33,684
It always ends up
either overcooked or undercooked.

1255
00:47:33,750 --> 00:47:36,587
-So I do want to copy this one.
-The <i>chashu</i>.

1256
00:47:36,653 --> 00:47:39,489
-Thank you.
-Sam continues to rise and rise.

1257
00:47:39,556 --> 00:47:42,392
Next, please try Chef Ho-young's dish.

1258
00:47:42,860 --> 00:47:45,829
RAMEN MADE WITH WARM CHICKEN BROTH
AND A VARIETY OF TOPPINGS

1259
00:47:46,797 --> 00:47:50,033
FLUFFY KELP MERINGUE ADDED FOR EXTRA UMAMI

1260
00:47:50,100 --> 00:47:52,236
I really want to know what that's like.

1261
00:47:52,302 --> 00:47:54,771
-Yes.
-He had the idea to top it with a cloud.

1262
00:47:55,272 --> 00:47:57,374
Whenever I go to a ramen place,

1263
00:47:57,441 --> 00:47:59,276
I always take a quick picture
before I eat.

1264
00:47:59,343 --> 00:48:01,078
Because the noodles can get soggy.

1265
00:48:01,144 --> 00:48:04,815
First, have a spoon of that foam.

1266
00:48:04,882 --> 00:48:08,252
<i>I mixed it with water</i>
<i>that soaked kelp and dried clam meat,</i>

1267
00:48:08,318 --> 00:48:09,987
so it'll be quite savory.

1268
00:48:10,053 --> 00:48:13,490
-So try that first, and then mix it in.
-Just the foam first?

1269
00:48:14,458 --> 00:48:16,827
First, try the foam, and then mix it in.

1270
00:48:18,462 --> 00:48:20,530
Is the foam already delicious?

1271
00:48:21,331 --> 00:48:22,199
Is it flavored?

1272
00:48:22,266 --> 00:48:24,101
I've never had anything like this,

1273
00:48:24,167 --> 00:48:25,836
but it's so good.

1274
00:48:26,270 --> 00:48:27,104
MOUTH GETS DRY

1275
00:48:27,170 --> 00:48:28,305
I can taste

1276
00:48:28,372 --> 00:48:30,340
everything he mentioned.

1277
00:48:30,674 --> 00:48:33,844
FULL OF SAVORY KELP AND CLAM FLAVORS

1278
00:48:35,312 --> 00:48:36,346
MMM

1279
00:48:36,413 --> 00:48:38,749
-So it doesn't taste plain?
-Now, mix it in.

1280
00:48:38,815 --> 00:48:40,317
Once you mix everything in,

1281
00:48:40,384 --> 00:48:44,288
the chicken broth
and the bonito broth will come together

1282
00:48:44,354 --> 00:48:46,723
to make the soup even more flavorful.

1283
00:48:46,790 --> 00:48:48,625
My gosh.

1284
00:48:48,692 --> 00:48:50,961
MIXING

1285
00:48:52,262 --> 00:48:53,330
Is that pasta?

1286
00:48:53,530 --> 00:48:54,364
CHUCKLE…

1287
00:48:55,198 --> 00:48:57,401
"Is that pasta?"

1288
00:48:57,701 --> 00:48:59,569
GETS ANXIOUS AND SHOWS HIS CANINE

1289
00:48:59,636 --> 00:49:00,904
Doesn't look like it.

1290
00:49:00,971 --> 00:49:02,172
-Isn't it pasta?
-Is it udon?

1291
00:49:02,439 --> 00:49:03,907
PLEASED

1292
00:49:04,341 --> 00:49:05,575
GRABS A HUGE CHUNK OF NOODLES

1293
00:49:06,543 --> 00:49:07,444
SLURP

1294
00:49:07,511 --> 00:49:09,680
As always, everything looks
so delicious today.

1295
00:49:09,746 --> 00:49:11,782
-It looks good.
-Whoa.

1296
00:49:11,848 --> 00:49:14,518
-What a rough day. It looks good.
-I want some.

1297
00:49:14,584 --> 00:49:16,320
-Try the soup.
-It looks great.

1298
00:49:16,386 --> 00:49:18,221
I mean, he really loves noodles.

1299
00:49:19,056 --> 00:49:20,424
And he has had a lot.

1300
00:49:21,158 --> 00:49:22,092
I like

1301
00:49:22,159 --> 00:49:24,761
how it has a strong taste of seafood.

1302
00:49:24,995 --> 00:49:25,862
FEELING PROUD

1303
00:49:25,929 --> 00:49:27,030
This one

1304
00:49:27,097 --> 00:49:30,300
had a strong flavor of chicken,

1305
00:49:30,367 --> 00:49:34,805
while this one tastes like
a very refreshing clam soup.

1306
00:49:36,673 --> 00:49:37,908
-It's so delicious.
<i>-</i>The <i>chashu.</i>

1307
00:49:37,975 --> 00:49:39,810
He made that <i>chashu</i> in no time too.

1308
00:49:40,344 --> 00:49:42,179
A BIG BITE

1309
00:49:42,846 --> 00:49:44,181
HOW'S THE 15-MINUTE CHASHU?

1310
00:49:44,247 --> 00:49:46,350
I hope it's good.

1311
00:49:46,917 --> 00:49:48,151
OH!

1312
00:49:48,218 --> 00:49:51,154
I thought it'd be too sweet
because you used a lot of cooking wine,

1313
00:49:52,356 --> 00:49:53,323
but I like how it isn't.

1314
00:49:53,390 --> 00:49:55,659
I prefer <i>chashu</i> that isn't sweet.

1315
00:49:55,726 --> 00:49:57,728
That's amazing.
He used a lot of cooking wine.

1316
00:49:57,794 --> 00:49:59,930
-What about the marinated egg?
-The egg. It's in there.

1317
00:49:59,997 --> 00:50:02,032
-Yes, it's in there.
-He should cut it in half.

1318
00:50:02,099 --> 00:50:04,534
Why didn't you cut it before serving?
Was this intentional?

1319
00:50:04,601 --> 00:50:06,236
There's fun in splitting the egg.

1320
00:50:06,303 --> 00:50:08,071
There's fun in it?

1321
00:50:08,138 --> 00:50:09,306
-I'll cut it.
-Feel that fun.

1322
00:50:09,373 --> 00:50:10,273
Whoa.

1323
00:50:10,540 --> 00:50:11,441
WHAT?

1324
00:50:11,508 --> 00:50:12,609
It slides in nicely.

1325
00:50:12,676 --> 00:50:14,177
PERFECTLY SOFT-BOILED

1326
00:50:14,244 --> 00:50:16,713
-That is so perfect.
-That was fun.

1327
00:50:16,780 --> 00:50:17,614
That was fun.

1328
00:50:17,681 --> 00:50:20,050
He cooked it until the point
that the yolk doesn't go runny.

1329
00:50:20,117 --> 00:50:22,652
Once he puts it into his mouth, it's over.

1330
00:50:22,719 --> 00:50:24,421
-It's like a blanket.
-Nothing else matters.

1331
00:50:24,488 --> 00:50:25,455
Man.

1332
00:50:26,390 --> 00:50:27,924
STOMPING BECAUSE IT'S SO GOOD

1333
00:50:29,326 --> 00:50:31,228
LOVING IT

1334
00:50:31,294 --> 00:50:34,231
-He stomps his feet.
-I'm dying to try it right now.

1335
00:50:34,297 --> 00:50:35,966
-He looks so happy.
-I'm dying to try it.

1336
00:50:36,800 --> 00:50:38,168
I always

1337
00:50:38,235 --> 00:50:40,437
spend a day at the longest

1338
00:50:40,504 --> 00:50:43,006
and about six to seven hours
at the shortest

1339
00:50:43,073 --> 00:50:46,410
to make these eggs
by soaking them in sauce in a bag.

1340
00:50:46,476 --> 00:50:48,912
-But you made it in that short time?
-Does it taste the same?

1341
00:50:48,979 --> 00:50:50,847
The trick is to leave it in ice

1342
00:50:50,914 --> 00:50:54,184
to let it cool quickly, because that way,
the sauce seeps in faster.

1343
00:50:54,251 --> 00:50:56,353
The key is cooling it down.

1344
00:50:58,789 --> 00:51:00,023
I want some.

1345
00:51:00,090 --> 00:51:02,325
Now, let's try Chef Sam's dish,

1346
00:51:02,392 --> 00:51:05,662
Why Do You Only, Only Make Noodles?

1347
00:51:06,430 --> 00:51:07,798
SLURP

1348
00:51:07,864 --> 00:51:09,433
-Mmm!
-It tastes like…

1349
00:51:09,499 --> 00:51:11,001
-Whoa.
-It smells good.

1350
00:51:11,334 --> 00:51:13,570
EVERYONE SOUNDS AMAZED

1351
00:51:13,637 --> 00:51:14,471
What is it?

1352
00:51:14,538 --> 00:51:16,139
-It's good.
-This is…

1353
00:51:16,206 --> 00:51:17,474
-Why is it so good?
-It is.

1354
00:51:18,008 --> 00:51:18,842
SLURRRP

1355
00:51:19,843 --> 00:51:22,412
He used many different ingredients,

1356
00:51:22,479 --> 00:51:24,481
yet it tastes very clean.

1357
00:51:24,548 --> 00:51:29,286
I don't taste that distinct flour flavor
that I always do when I eat ramen,

1358
00:51:29,352 --> 00:51:32,289
and it just tastes nice and clean.

1359
00:51:32,355 --> 00:51:33,423
It's good.

1360
00:51:33,490 --> 00:51:36,893
It didn't taste like the ramen I expected.

1361
00:51:36,960 --> 00:51:40,163
It felt as if I were eating it
in a flower garden.

1362
00:51:40,230 --> 00:51:42,032
It felt like spring. Spring ramen.

1363
00:51:42,099 --> 00:51:43,567
-Spring ramen?
-Yes.

1364
00:51:44,868 --> 00:51:46,870
The broth could've been too rich,

1365
00:51:46,937 --> 00:51:51,074
so he added the herbs
and made the flavor more refreshing.

1366
00:51:51,141 --> 00:51:54,277
I couldn't even find a moment
to get sick of it. It was delicious.

1367
00:51:54,344 --> 00:51:56,213
It'd be even better cold.

1368
00:51:56,279 --> 00:51:57,848
-Yes.
-I agree.

1369
00:51:57,914 --> 00:52:00,250
Next, Chef Ho-young's dish,

1370
00:52:00,317 --> 00:52:02,352
-Now, this one.
-Do I Seem That, That Easy?

1371
00:52:02,419 --> 00:52:05,422
-He said to try this first. The meringue.
-The foam.

1372
00:52:06,356 --> 00:52:08,458
Mmm! This meringue is so good.

1373
00:52:09,459 --> 00:52:11,161
This adds lots of flavors.

1374
00:52:11,228 --> 00:52:12,496
Yes, I can taste it.

1375
00:52:14,397 --> 00:52:16,700
TOPPED WITH LOTS OF MERINGUE

1376
00:52:19,736 --> 00:52:20,770
Whoa.

1377
00:52:22,038 --> 00:52:23,173
The meringue foam

1378
00:52:23,707 --> 00:52:25,375
tastes like foam fish cake.

1379
00:52:26,510 --> 00:52:29,312
It has the fish cake flavor,

1380
00:52:29,379 --> 00:52:32,015
but it melts, so it's like foam fish cake.

1381
00:52:32,082 --> 00:52:33,984
It comes in softly like cappuccino,

1382
00:52:34,050 --> 00:52:36,153
but the umami hits you so hard.

1383
00:52:36,419 --> 00:52:37,420
NODS

1384
00:52:37,487 --> 00:52:40,290
How did he make this soup
in just 15 minutes?

1385
00:52:40,357 --> 00:52:41,591
It's extremely savory.

1386
00:52:42,526 --> 00:52:45,595
After all, the soup
is made with chicken broth, right?

1387
00:52:45,662 --> 00:52:47,531
And that feels like a blank canvas.

1388
00:52:47,597 --> 00:52:50,534
Depending on what you do,
the flavor changes drastically,

1389
00:52:50,600 --> 00:52:53,236
in a completely different direction.
The idea is fascinating.

1390
00:52:53,303 --> 00:52:56,773
Mothers usually won't let their children
eat too much <i>ramyeon</i>.

1391
00:52:56,840 --> 00:53:00,243
-But if it's a healthy ramen like this…
-This is a healthy dish.

1392
00:53:00,310 --> 00:53:02,646
If it's a little less salty.

1393
00:53:02,712 --> 00:53:04,047
Ye-eun, did you come alone?

1394
00:53:04,114 --> 00:53:06,416
YE-EUN, ARE YOU HERE TO EAT ALONE?

1395
00:53:06,483 --> 00:53:08,818
She continues to slurp and slurp
while listening to everyone.

1396
00:53:09,052 --> 00:53:10,086
GIGGLING

1397
00:53:10,153 --> 00:53:11,588
Let's chat a little.

1398
00:53:11,655 --> 00:53:14,191
-It was so good.
-It was?

1399
00:53:14,257 --> 00:53:17,661
All I have ever had was <i>tonkotsu</i> ramen,

1400
00:53:17,727 --> 00:53:20,363
so I just thought ramen was a heavy dish.

1401
00:53:20,430 --> 00:53:22,666
But this one was so light.
Also, as for the meringue,

1402
00:53:22,732 --> 00:53:25,502
I thought it'd taste too creamy,

1403
00:53:25,569 --> 00:53:28,104
but it tasted light and refreshing.

1404
00:53:28,171 --> 00:53:29,306
SHE'S RIGHT

1405
00:53:29,372 --> 00:53:31,875
-I'd eat Sam's ramen for lunch.
-Yes.

1406
00:53:31,942 --> 00:53:36,012
And I'd eat Ho-young's ramen for dinner
with a drink or as the hangover cure.

1407
00:53:36,313 --> 00:53:37,781
TWO RAMENS WITH DISTINCT FLAVORS

1408
00:53:37,847 --> 00:53:40,150
This is pretty tough.
These are way too different.

1409
00:53:40,717 --> 00:53:42,519
Yes, it's so hard.

1410
00:53:42,586 --> 00:53:44,854
-It'll be a matter of your preference.
-Yes.

1411
00:53:45,322 --> 00:53:46,890
THE MOMENT OF TRUTH

1412
00:53:46,957 --> 00:53:48,758
<i>Press one to pick Sam Kim,</i>

1413
00:53:48,825 --> 00:53:49,993
<i>and two for Jung Ho-young.</i>

1414
00:53:50,927 --> 00:53:53,396
Please press a button, Jun-young.

1415
00:53:53,463 --> 00:53:55,365
They both had deep flavors.

1416
00:53:57,400 --> 00:53:58,735
PRESSES

1417
00:53:58,802 --> 00:54:00,704
-I pressed one.
-You did?

1418
00:54:00,770 --> 00:54:02,372
That was a tough decision.

1419
00:54:02,439 --> 00:54:03,540
No regrets?

1420
00:54:03,607 --> 00:54:04,808
Gosh…

1421
00:54:04,874 --> 00:54:07,344
Well, you know,
the difference was literally

1422
00:54:07,410 --> 00:54:08,778
just a hair.

1423
00:54:08,845 --> 00:54:11,214
-Yes.
-That's what everyone says.

1424
00:54:11,281 --> 00:54:12,816
-They all say it's by a hair.
-Of course.

1425
00:54:12,882 --> 00:54:15,285
Which one of them became the winner?

1426
00:54:15,352 --> 00:54:16,586
Jun-young's choice!

1427
00:54:16,653 --> 00:54:18,521
Let's find out. Show us.

1428
00:54:18,588 --> 00:54:21,124
This was a ramen round.

1429
00:54:21,191 --> 00:54:23,827
Once besties, now sworn enemies.

1430
00:54:23,893 --> 00:54:25,829
In this ramen round,

1431
00:54:25,895 --> 00:54:28,898
will Chef Sam continue to keep
his winning streak?

1432
00:54:28,965 --> 00:54:30,934
Or will Ho-young

1433
00:54:31,001 --> 00:54:34,404
defeat Sam and win from behind?

1434
00:54:34,471 --> 00:54:37,374
The ramen enthusiast, Jun-young's choice!

1435
00:54:37,440 --> 00:54:39,042
Who's the winner?

1436
00:54:39,109 --> 00:54:42,279
Whose ramen did you prefer? Who won?

1437
00:54:42,345 --> 00:54:43,980
What's the result?

1438
00:54:44,180 --> 00:54:45,215
JUNG HO-YOUNG WINS

1439
00:54:45,282 --> 00:54:46,583
Jung Ho-young wins.

1440
00:54:46,816 --> 00:54:49,185
SAM KIM, DO I SEEM THAT, THAT EASY? WINS

1441
00:54:50,053 --> 00:54:52,188
IT WAS DIFFICULT TO PREDICT

1442
00:54:52,255 --> 00:54:55,558
-But his ramen was so good too.
-I knew it.

1443
00:54:55,625 --> 00:54:58,061
I really loved it.

1444
00:54:58,128 --> 00:55:00,730
And this was something
I could 100% recreate,

1445
00:55:00,797 --> 00:55:03,333
and something I would want to.

1446
00:55:03,400 --> 00:55:05,935
But the biggest shock for me
was the meringue.

1447
00:55:06,002 --> 00:55:08,405
-That was huge.
-It must've been shocking.

1448
00:55:08,471 --> 00:55:10,607
I've had so many ramens,

1449
00:55:10,674 --> 00:55:13,843
but this was the first time
I had it with meringue on top.

1450
00:55:13,910 --> 00:55:15,145
But it was there

1451
00:55:15,211 --> 00:55:18,815
not to balance out the richness,

1452
00:55:18,882 --> 00:55:23,086
but just to add the necessary flavors,
and then it disappeared.

1453
00:55:23,153 --> 00:55:25,288
-I was captivated.
-I see.

1454
00:55:25,889 --> 00:55:27,424
Thank you for the dishes.

1455
00:55:27,490 --> 00:55:30,593
-Ho-young got to break his losing streak.
-Yes.

1456
00:55:31,294 --> 00:55:33,697
Chef Sam, you kept taunting him.

1457
00:55:33,763 --> 00:55:35,198
UGH…

1458
00:55:35,265 --> 00:55:37,500
But Ho-young was much stronger
in the world of ramen.

1459
00:55:37,567 --> 00:55:40,904
So? Would you like
to face him in a pasta round next time?

1460
00:55:40,970 --> 00:55:43,106
-Yes, that sounds great.
-Do that.

1461
00:55:43,173 --> 00:55:45,475
I learned a lot
while putting this recipe together.

1462
00:55:45,542 --> 00:55:47,577
That was the first time
I've ever made ramen.

1463
00:55:47,644 --> 00:55:48,778
The first time?

1464
00:55:48,845 --> 00:55:51,715
-It was so good.
-I only knew it in theory, so I tried.

1465
00:55:51,781 --> 00:55:56,586
I had a lot of fun
learning about this new kind of dish.

1466
00:55:56,653 --> 00:55:58,421
The winner of this round

1467
