1567
00:59:48,251 --> 00:59:50,019
The dish I'm making is

1568
00:59:50,520 --> 00:59:54,724
Lee Jun-young, Will You Give Me a Star
After Eating This, Jun-young?

1569
00:59:56,025 --> 00:59:58,661
-That's Chef Jong-won's style.
-Yes, it's his style.

1570
00:59:58,728 --> 01:00:01,197
-He did this often.
-That heart.

1571
01:00:01,264 --> 01:00:02,732
-Jong-won's style.
-That's me today.

1572
01:00:02,799 --> 01:00:04,167
-And the heart.
-The heart.

1573
01:00:04,233 --> 01:00:06,002
Yes, I have to do the heart.

1574
01:00:06,069 --> 01:00:08,838
I prepared something called fricassée,

1575
01:00:08,905 --> 01:00:11,574
one of the most
popular chicken dishes in France,

1576
01:00:11,641 --> 01:00:15,244
-allegedly. So I'll make that.
-She doesn't really know.

1577
01:00:15,311 --> 01:00:17,013
-You should say you know.
-The ingredients

1578
01:00:17,080 --> 01:00:19,282
all have French vibes.

1579
01:00:19,349 --> 01:00:21,250
So I'm definitely a Parisienne today.

1580
01:00:21,317 --> 01:00:22,619
I have a feeling

1581
01:00:22,685 --> 01:00:25,722
